title: mini blintzes
directions: Remove crust from each slice of bread and flatten each slice with a rolling pin.
Cream egg yolk, the 1/4 cup sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons filling on each slice and roll up jelly-roll style.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon to melted and cooled butter.
Dip each roll into butter mixture.
"Flash" freeze on cookie sheet for 1 hour, then freeze in plastic bag.

title: edna's herbed cream cheese
directions: Blend garlic, onion, salt and mustard.
Add cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, olives, thyme and Tabasco and blend.
Sprinkle with parsley or chives.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, mustard and pepper; stir in macaroni.
In cup, combine breadcrumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over macaroni mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Skin and bone cooked chicken breasts.
Place broccoli in casserole and top with slices of chicken meat.
Combine undiluted soups with mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.
This dish may be frozen before baking.
To serve, return to room temperature and bake.
Serves 8.

title: frozen banana mousse
directions: Peel bananas and place in plastic bag.
Freeze at least 6 hours.
Remove from freezer and cut each into 5 or 6 pieces.
In the work bowl or blender, blend/mix banana pieces and remaining ingredients until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: crisp fried streak-of-lean
directions: Freeze a
x	3-inch	chunk
of
streak-of-lean meat. Slice thin.
Wash and boil, covered, at least 5 minutes. Drain and pat dry.
Dip in buttermilk and into flour (self-rising). Fry to a golden brown in a skillet with 1/2-inch oil on medium heat.
Drain on
paper	towel.	It's
crisp and golden brown. Serve with
hot biscuits, sweet corn, sliced tomatoes and iced tea.
Makes the best meal.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix everything, but eggs and melted butter.
Add eggs last. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Mix sugar and spices into beaten eggs.
Stir in chilled orange and lemon juices.
Cut ice cream in chunks; place in punch bowl.
Slowly pour gingerale in bowl.
Gently stir in egg mixture. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and rind; add egg yolk, sugar and butter. Then add flour, egg yolks and milk.
Then fold beaten egg whites into batter.
Pour into pie shell.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: oriental steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into small cubes and brown.
Add onion, celery and soy sauce and blend well.
Add both cans of soup and 1 cup water. Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour hot steak mixture over rice and serve.

title: pea salad
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl, having chilled them well ahead of time. Add seasonings to taste. Add enough mayonnaise to cover well (approx. 3 heaping tablespoons) and toss lightly. Sprinkle top lightly with paprika.

title: cucumber onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mix well and chill.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix together in order.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry cups
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla, eggs and sugar together on high speed.
Place wafer in bottom of 2-inch paper cup in muffin pan. Fill cups 3/4 full of mixture.
Cook at 375° for 15 minutes, until tops are smooth and dry looking.
Let cool completely, then place 1 teaspoon of cherry mixture on top.
Refrigerate until served. More excellent party food!

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese well.
Add drained pineapple, package of strawberries and Cool Whip.
Fold in sliced bananas and nuts.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients
well.
Add enough water so it will drop from spoon easily.
Fry in deep fat.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown together the ground beef and butter.
Add tomato sauce; set aside. Mix together the cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
Place layer of noodles in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Pour half of the cheese mixture over noodles; alternately add noodles and rest of cheese mixture.
Add meat and tomato sauce on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: You will need rolled rump roast (size you need).
Put in oven cooking bag.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Tie up bag.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour per pound.
Take roast out of bag and cover; let cool, then slice.
Take juice from bag.
Add enough water to make gravy; also use some beef broth (canned).
I add some Kitchen Bouquet.
Bring all ingredients to rolling boil and use cornstarch to thicken.
Add a little salt if needed.
You can put your beef slices in your gravy.
Cut your bread diagonally.
Lay on plate. Put slices of beef on bread, then gravy over all.

title: ms. clara's oyster cornbread dressing(lawrence's grandmother)
directions: Saute peppers, onions and celery in small amount of butter. Toast bread and crumble up along with cornbread in large casserole or roasting pan.
Pour enough broth over crumbled bread to make soft.
Add sauteed peppers, onions and celery.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and sage.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly, adding desired amount of chicken broth to make moist.

title: seasoning for green beans(canned)
directions: Mix and cook for 20 minutes.

title: easter eggs(basic recipe)
directions: Beat well the first 4 ingredients.
You may add coconut, fruit and nuts or peanut butter.
Shape and dip in melted chocolate and wax.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat the eggs until well blended.
Stir in the cooking oil and vanilla; blend in the sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Slowly add to egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 or less minutes in preheated oven at 400°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: teriyaki "pope" chops
directions: Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add garlic last.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt; add to beaten eggs.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked 9 to 10-inch pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; chop and save broth.
Brown peppers and onions in oil.
Add mushrooms and heat.
Cook noodles in some of the broth.
Make white sauce of flour, oil and 2 cups broth.
Add cream of mushroom soup and heat.
Add all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Put into greased casserole dish; top with Swiss cheese.
Cook in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: carrot bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. In large bowl, with spoon, mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly; stir in oil and vanilla extract.
Stir egg mixture, shredded carrots, walnuts and applesauce into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.

title: oatmeal whoopie pies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add cinnamon and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Add soda to boiling water; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Blend margarine and Bisquick together with fork.
Add rest of the ingredients and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Fill half full.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until slightly brown on top.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Spread in bottom of 11 x 7 inch dish.
Spread crumbled bread over sausage.
Beat eggs well, add milk.
Pour over bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate loaf cake with miracle whip
directions: Dissolve soda in cold water; mix together sugar, cocoa and water with soda dissolved in it.
Add flour, vanilla and Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a cookie sheet.
Bake and let cool. Top with a mixture of cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Top with strawberry glaze and any kind of fresh fruit.
Then top with nuts and whipped cream, if desired.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, pepper and salt together.
Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Pound flour mixture into meat with edge of saucer. Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Layer steak and onion in greased casserole or roasting pan. Spoon soup over top. Add water and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or lower temperature for longer time. This is good made in a slow cooker all day, too.

title: russian dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: ketchup
directions: Boil tomatoes and onions until soft.
Drain in jelly bag 4 hours.
Put through sieve, discard juice.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients; add to tomato mixture, boil 10 more minutes.
Put boiling mixture in hot jars and seal.

title: cheddar and beer cracker spread
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except salt.
Puree until smooth.
Season to taste with salt.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: crepes
directions: To clarify butter:
Microwave 1/2 cup butter until butter creates a fluffy, take off top.
Clear amber liquid is part you use.
Discard residue on bottom.

title: pumpkin pie (custard)
directions: Mix pumpkin and 4 eggs in a large bowl; stir in dry ingredients followed by milk and melted butter.
Put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Combine flours, cornmeal and vegetable oil.
Mix well. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add bouillon to flour mixture to make a stiff dough. Roll onto a floured surface. Cut out shapes with cookie cutter or glass.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, combine pasta and vegetables.
Add salad dressing to taste.
Mix well.
May sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired. If salad is refrigerated a few hours or overnight, shake or stir well (some more salad dressing may need to be added).

title: pie crust
directions: Beat the egg in a cup and finish filling the cup with water and also a little vinegar.
Makes about 3 double crust pies. Very easy to handle.
Doesn't crack and can be rerolled.

title: vanilla muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place greased muffin pan in hot oven. Beat sugar and egg together.
Add flour, milk, baking powder, butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill hot pans full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: homemade "cream" soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.

title: banana chip muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake until done.

title: white bread
directions: Combine yeast, water and sugar.
Add salt, egg and oil; mix real good.
Add flour; mix real good again.
Let rise in bowl; punch down.
Let rise again; punch down and put in 2 loaf pans that are well greased.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let sit 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Lay bread on side to cool; this will help it stay moist.

title: "no fuss" banana bread
directions: In mixing bowl combine sugar, butter and egg.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Pour mixture into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: o'charley's spinach dip
directions: Thaw, drain and squeeze dry the spinach. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and heat in the microwave until hot, stirring frequently. Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 5 cups.

title: coco not cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and coconut extract.
Beat well.
Stir in potato flakes and biscuit mix. Put on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Make 3/4 inch balls for pretty cookies or drop from teaspoon.
Bake to very light brown, about 12 minutes.
Watch or they will get too brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 50.

title: clams fantasy
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Saute minced onion and pepper in butter. Add Old Bay seasoning and cracker crumbs and egg.
Make into stuffing.

title: divinity
directions: Combine syrup, water and salt and stir in sugar until dissolved.
Boil to hard boil stage.
Beat egg
whites until stiff.
Pour syrup on egg whites (slowly) while beating.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: pralines
directions: Place all ingredients in heavy boiler except nuts.
Cook until mixture reaches soft boil stage (candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Let cool a little (but still very warm). Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: sharon's famous pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well.
Stir in hot melted butter.
Stir in corn syrups, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Boil shrimp, then mince them in blender.
Add all other ingredients; mix well and shape into round ball.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Put all fruit into a bowl.
Do not drain.
Add lemon pudding mix.
Let stand for about 1 hour before serving.

title: ribbon dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, crushed pecans, sugar and butter. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a loaf and place it in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Line pie crust with pecan pieces or raisins.
Bake until starts to brown.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust and bake about 20 minutes in a 325° oven or until golden brown. Top with Cool Whip.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter, lemon, cream cheese and eggs, one at a time.
Fold in cake flour; add dry whipped topping.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: Make a brown roux.
In a large pot add flour and oil and cook until roux is dark brown.
Add onions and green onions.
Cook in flour mixture for about 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and okra. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
Bring to a boil.
Add turkey and smoked sausage that has been cooked and drained.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: boneless pork loin roast
directions: Remove loin from package and rinse well. Sprinkle with salt and put into baking pan. Do not cover. Bake at 350 degrees until done. Done when juices are clear (about 2 hours). Remove loin to serving platter. Place baking pan on stove burner and add 2 cups water and bring to boil. Add sliced onion. Stir together 1/2 C water and 3 Tbsp. corn starch until smooth. Add to baking pan. Cook until thickened. Remove from heat. Slice roast and put into a deep corning ware dish and pour gravy over roast. Serve.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Place flavored syrup and milk in a tall glass and stir.
Add ice cream and pour club soda until glass is almost filled. Garnish with whip cream and cherry.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring to a boil, then simmer for about 30 minutes.
Can add water, if needed.

title: gaston beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil or butter over high heat.
Sprinkle meat with flour.
Combine garlic, onion, bouillon, tomato sauce, peppercorns, cloves, parsley and bay leaf.
Heat until boiling.
Pour ingredients over meat and simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is very tender.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Combine all ingredients except French fried onions.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate raspberry nut bars
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Beat in flour a little at a time.
Spread batter on an oiled jelly roll tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take from oven and lightly spread with raspberry jam.
Top with chocolate bits.
Put back in oven for a few minutes so you can spread the chocolate. Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts.
Press in gently; let it cool thoroughly. Cut gently into 70 pieces with pizza cutter.

title: baked parmesan fish
directions: Roll up fillets and place, seam side down, in ungreased baking dish.
Mix sour cream, paprika, tarragon leaves, salt and pepper. Spread over fish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes. Sprinkle with onions.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry. Add onion, tomatoes, bacon, spaghetti and half cheese. Simmer 15 minutes (covered). Pour into baking dish; add rest of grated cheese on top. Add 1 can tomato paste on top. Cook 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies(really good)
directions: Mix one box of brownie mix and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix filling of cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over first brownie mix.
Mix second box of brownie mix and spread over filling.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
(Test: It may need to bake longer.)
You can add chocolate bits or walnuts.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased glass dish, size 11 x 7-inch.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tahitian salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese.
Add fruit and whipped topping. Decorate with cherries.

title: swiss treats
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into creamed mixture. Add nuts, chopped cherries, coconut and chocolate pieces.
Spread dough in a greased 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool slightly; cut into bars.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put in greased and floured loaf pans. Store in refrigerator.
Freezes well.

title: white mustard sauce
directions: Season the white sauce with mustard, salt, vinegar and sugar.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil with garlic clove added.
Before turning, sprinkle chicken with seasonings.
When chicken is nicely browned, remove garlic.
Add mushrooms and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook until sauce is reduced and chicken is tender.
Good with spaghetti or rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: apple dip
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to softened cream cheese. Mix until creamy. Add walnuts. Serve with sliced apples.

title: potato salad(serves 100)
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: bread-one hour loaf
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast over warm water.
Sprinkle sugar over yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Measure out salt, flour and salad oil.
Beat yeast until dissolved, add oil, 1 cup flour and salt. Beat hard.
Add remaining flour and stir to form a ball.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead 20 strokes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Shape as desired.
Let rise to twice its size in warm place, covered, bake at 375° until golden.
Takes 1 hour from start to serving.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pan on medium high, cook hamburger with salt and pepper.
Using a fork, chop the hamburger into real small pieces while it's cooking.
When hamburger is cooked, turn heat down to low and add the tomato sauce, paste and soup.
Fill each can full of water; add to mixture.
Stir real good until smooth.
Keep on low heat (do not boil).
Cook lasagna for about 20 minutes, until soft.
Place in a 10 x 13-inch pan one layer of lasagna to a layer of sauce until gone.
Top with cheese.
Place in oven just until melted at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: "presidential cabbage casserole"
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Cook rice in water for 20 minutes.
Combine ground beef, onions and rice in bowl.
Add tomato soup (without water).
Cook cabbage in large pot with approximately 4 cups water until tender.
Core cabbage and cut leaves into strips.
Place cooked cabbage, ground beef and rice in casserole dish.
Add tomato juice to mixture until very moist.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: In a large pot, cook the rice with the milk and margarine on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
When well cooked, add sugar, salt, lemon and beaten egg yolks.
Stir well and cook for another 3 minutes.
Serve cool.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: honey pecan bread
directions: Combine 3 cups white flour and whole wheat flour.

In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour mixture, salt and yeast. Combine water, honey, margarine and cottage cheese in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°). Margarine does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour mixture. Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in quick oats, remaining flour mixture and enough additional white flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to greased top.
Cover bowl; let rise in a warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Punch dough down.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead in pecans.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each into a loaf and place in two greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans or into balls and place in two greased 8-inch layer cake pans.
Lightly grease tops of loaves.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: hot cauliflower
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pack jars with 2 hot yellow wax peppers or 3 to 4 small hot peppers or 2 to 3 hot cherry peppers, raw cauliflower florets, 1 clove garlic and 1 teaspoon dill seed.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over raw cauliflower into jars.
Seal.
Place in canner and let come to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove.
Let stand in jars before using to allow hot peppers to work through mixture for 6 weeks until 3 months.
Longer they set, the hotter they get.
You can also put raw cucumber slices, onion slices, canned olives or green tomatoes in jars.
Jab green tomatoes two or three times with fork.

title: tony's shrimp dip
directions: Heat and mix the cream cheese, butter and Tabasco until blended.
Add onions and shrimp.
Turn off heat; stir until cooled.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Add oleo; cook over low heat until thick.
Add coconut and stir well.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue.
Bake until brown.
Serve cold.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Arrange single layer of bread in bottom of buttered pan. Cover with ham and cheese.
Repeat layers of meat and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, onion, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Serves about 16.

title: smothered chicken or steak
directions: Add 1/2 cup Crisco or oil to iron skillet, heat.
Roll chicken or steak in flour.
Season with salt and pepper; brown each piece until golden brown.
When all is brown, add glass of water.
Let cook in oven until it makes its own gravy.
May have to add more water or use milk instead of water.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the dates and let cool.
Add the butter, sugar and eggs to the date mixture.
Then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: sweet-and-sour dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar. Chill. Shake and serve over salad.

title: smothered venison steak
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Dredge steak in flour and add to oil.
Sprinkle with tenderizer and pepper.
Brown on both sides.
Remove meat.
Add potatoes, onions, soda and soup to frying pan.
Lay steaks on top of potato mixture.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 2 hours or put in 325° oven for 2 hours.
Serves 2 to 3.
Preparation Time: 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cook Irish potato well done.
Mash potato and start working in confectioners sugar until it is like stiff dough.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Make into a roll, then slice.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix 1 package jello with 1 cup hot orange juice.
Let set until partially firm.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 carton Cool Whip with electric mixer.
Mix in partially firm jello. Fold in mandarin oranges.
Pour into container and let set until firm. Mix 1 package orange jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup orange juice and let set until partially firm.
Pour over first mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Cook onion in half the butter for 5 minutes.
Add to crumbs, then add beef, nutmeg, salt, pepper, milk and egg.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Saute in remaining butter until brown.
Put bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour over meat balls. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove meat and thicken remaining liquid with flour mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until smooth and thick; pour over meat balls.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Melt butter in dish and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caroline's dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: danish tea cookies
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll dough out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out small, round cookies (about 1 1/2-inches in diameter).
Pat each side with sugar.
Prick each cookie with a fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Put frozen bread dough in refrigerator to defrost overnight. Next day, butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Take first loaf and break off 50 cent size pieces and place in pan.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; toss.
Combine the last 6 ingredients.
Pour over the first.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours, remove garlic.

title: neapolitan yogurt parfait
directions: Spoon 1/4 cup strawberry yogurt into each of 4 parfait glasses.
Crumble 1 cookie on yogurt in each glass.
Top each with 1/4 cup of vanilla yogurt.
Top each with another crumbled cookie and 1/4 cup of the strawberry yogurt.
Freeze 45 minutes.
Garnish each parfait with a fresh strawberry.

title: smoky oven barbecued chicken
directions: Cook garlic in hot butter over medium heat until lightly browned in 1-quart saucepan.
Add catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: favorite meat loaf(microwave; 6 servings)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard in a small bowl. Set aside.
Combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Place into a large ring mold or a 2-quart microproof round casserole with an inverted 6 ounce custard cup in center.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Insert temperature probe in section of meat loaf, in center portion.
Plug in temperature probe.
Cook on High (Max power). Set at 160°.
Cover and let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: ritz cracker pie(better known as apple pie)
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the water, sugar and tartar.
Drop 22 whole Ritz crackers, 2 or 3 at a time.
Do not stir.
Boil 2 minutes.
Place in unbaked pie crust.
Dot generously with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Put top crust on, making vents for steam to escape.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, for 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm with cheese or ice cream.

title: chilies and cheese souffle
directions: Shred cheeses and put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan, buttered. Sprinkle with green chilies, pour beaten eggs over cheeses, sprinkle
with chili powder.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes and cut into bite size pieces, about 1 1/2 x 1 1/2 inches.

title: rhett butler's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and Five Alive juice.
Fill 1 gallon jug to about 3/4 full.
Add water to make 3/4 full.
Freeze overnight. Take out of jug and add 7-Up to taste.

title: june bugs
directions: Combine butter and cheese; beat until smooth.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Add to cheese mixture; mix well.
Cut dates in half crosswise; wrap each half with dough.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool on wire racks. Yield: 50 appetizers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut or tear bread into cubes.
Place in large bowl.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk, raisins and remaining ingredients.
Mix with bread.
Pour into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour (uncovered l5 minutes more) at 350°.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Boil for few minutes and pour in baked pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake for 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Prepare fruits; mix and place in large bowl.
Soak overnight with grape juice.
Sift spices and flour together 3 times.
Cream butter; add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs and flour alternately, carefully mixing after each addition.
Add nuts gradually, mixing them well through the batter,
small amount at a time, then the fruit and grape juice and mix well.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased, lined pan.
Bake on 2nd shelf at 275° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, depending on your oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and cool. Bone and chop in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti in broth. Saute garlic, pepper, celery and onion until tender.
Add soup and cook 15 minutes.
(May need to add a very small amount of water to this mixture.)
In baking dish, place a layer of spaghetti, layer of chicken and layer of sauce. Repeat layers and top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with salad.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes as for fries.
Place in center of large square of aluminum foil.
Add cream.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, parsley and cheese.
Wrap in foil, tightly.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked bean stew
directions: Brown bacon; remove and crumble.
Add onion rings to bacon drippings along with garlic.
Cook until transparent.
Add other sauce ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add beans and bacon.
Put into casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugarless strawberry jam
directions: Put pineapple in a little hot water to soften.
Blend with 1 cup strawberries until blended.
Add the remaining strawberries and blend until it's the consistency of jam.
Freeze.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients all together and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into ungreased jelly roll pan (11 1/2 x 17-inch). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion soup mix
directions: In a storage container with a tight-fitting lid, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Seal tightly.
Store in a cool, dry place for up to 6 months.
Stir or shake well before each use. Makes 18 tablespoons (about 1 cup).
Five tablespoons equals a 1.25 ounce package of onion soup.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and veggies evenly in dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Pour evenly over chicken. Combine baking mix, milk and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour mix over other ingredients.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place margarine or butter in baking dish to melt.
Mix the sugar with fruit (set aside).
Make batter of sifted flour, baking powder, pinch of salt, sugar and milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine or butter (do not stir).
Place fruit mix on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add melted margarine and blend well.
Stir in eggs, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: company chicken
directions: Place 1 slice of cheese on each breast and put in baking dish. Combine soup and wine; spread over breasts.
Sprinkle dressing over and drizzle butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: v's raspberry torte cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake cake as directed in two round pans.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans first.
Beat the pudding, milk and sour cream at low speed until blended, about 2 minutes. Stir in orange peel.
Let stand until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes. Split cake layers to make 4 layers.
Spread 2/3 cup of pudding mixture to the edges.
Top with 2/3 cup of fruit.
Repeat twice. Frost the side with whipped topping (Cool Whip).
Refrigerate to keep cool.

title: caramel marshmallows
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in double boiler.
Dip marshmallows in caramel, coating well.
Roll in Rice Krispies. Chill until set.

title: western omelet with mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Fry onions and peppers until tender. Then add mushrooms, and ham then cook to desired doneness.
Beat eggs one at a time, and add them to pan.
Stir mixture, cooking until done.
Serves 2.
Preparation time: 1/2 hour.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix well cake mix, butter or margarine and egg and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs, vanilla, pecans and coconut and pour over crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix warm water with yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and flour; mix well.
Add egg and oil and mix well. Gradually add 3 or 4 cups flour until dough is stiff.
Cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate overnight.
Dough will keep 5 days in refrigerator if cloth is kept damp.
Use amount desired and refrigerate remaining dough.
Work into balls and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° approximately 12 minutes.

title: julienne beets
directions: Shred cooked beets on shredder into thin strips.
Saute in margarine.
Season with salt, lemon juice, sugar and optional white pepper.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into 6 patties. Pan-fry, broil or grill until done, about 5 minutes per side.

title: spice cake
directions: Bake in layers and frost.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Mix next 5 ingredients; add to chicken mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with chicken soup.
(Refrigerate until next day, if desired.)
Top with crushed chips and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry tang salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and set aside.
Gradually blend mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Slowly add Jell-O to creamed mixture, blending until smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add drained pineapple, banana, pecans and coconut. Fold in whipped cream and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: special ending dessert
directions: Whisk yogurt and pineapple including juice together.
Add pudding and whisk until well blended.

title: hot hors d'oeuvre
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler. Mix in sausage and Bisquick. Form into balls the size of walnuts. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. These freeze very well. Freeze on cookie sheet, remove and store in bags in freezer.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour melted margarine over sugar.
Beat eggs, milk, coconut and vanilla in a bowl with sugar and margarine.
Mix all together well.
Put in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until coconut is golden brown.

title: layered tossed salad
directions: Place salad items and bacon in layers.
Mix together the mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Top the salad with this dressing. Do not mix in!
Cover tightly and refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: west virginia delight
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dried black-eyed pea croquettes
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Heat 1/2 inch of fat in skillet.
Drop by spoonfuls and fry until browned on both sides. Drain on paper towels or brown paper.
If mix is too dry, add pea juice or milk.

title: craft clay
directions: Mix and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Turn out dough on counter.
Cover with damp cloth until you use or keep in a container.
To harden, heat oven to 350°.
Turn off; put shapes on cookie sheet and leave in cooling oven.
For play only, not edible.

title: lion house taffy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and glycerine in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil and cook to a temperature of 258°.
Remove from heat and let stand for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter and stir vigorously until butter is melted. Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool until lukewarm taffy can be handled comfortably. Take a small piece of taffy and stretch and fold until it turns white.
Long strips may be cut and wrapped in pieces of wax paper or plastic wrap.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, break lettuce into small pieces.
Layer ingredients in order given. (Do not cook or thaw peas.) Mix together Miracle Whip and sugar. Spread on top, sealing edges. Make 24 hours ahead. Top with grated cheese before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and spinach.
Add onion soup.
Enjoy with cut up vegetables.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a medium bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Beat on low speed about 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer graham crackers, half of the pudding mixture, another layer of crackers and the remaining pudding mixture.
Top with a third layer of crackers.
Spread frosting on top. Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Beat with electric mixer for 5 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan or angel cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes in pan before turning out on plate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Add jello, stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberries.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes; pour into 8 inch pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.
Top with cool whip or ice cream when serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar and milk.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into shell.
You can freeze, if desired.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: mandarin-pineapple dessert
directions: In a large bowl, mix fruit, cottage cheese and dry jello powder. Mix in nuts, then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour to chill.

title: excellent play dough
directions: Mix in frying pan.
Cook just a couple minutes until it turns into play dough.
Cool.
Store tightly covered.
You can add a few drops food coloring for color.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in bowl all ingredients except for sauce. Stuff pasta shells with cheese mixture.
Place in lightly greased lasagne pan (10 x 13-inch).
Add onion to Ragu sauce in saucepan. Heat on medium until onion is tender.
Pour sauce over stuffed shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: never-fail microwave fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a large 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Add milk and butter; do not stir!
Cook on High 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir and add nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with topping.
Spread into the pie crusts, then spread pie filling over.
Place in refrigerator until required.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Mix well vanilla wafer crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff. Swirl meringue over crumb crust.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Spread berries over meringue.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions, adding lemon juice.
Spread over berries and chill.

title: beth's beef stroganoff
directions: Tenderize meat with meat mallet.
Cut into thin 1-inch strips. Moisten meat with a small amount of water.
Roll meat in flour and brown in oleo over medium heat.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, soup, salt and pepper to taste and sour cream to meat.
Simmer covered for 25 minutes.
Gradually add water, if needed, to keep mixture at gravy consistency.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: texas peas
directions: Pick peas (black-eyes, crowders, purple hulls or other). Shell promptly, then rinse well.
Place in saucepan with water to cover along with other ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring often.
(Add water as needed.)

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8-inch casserole dish.
Stir dry ingredients.
Add milk, stirring until just blended.
Spoon carefully over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour the sweetened fruit over the batter; do not stir.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cube steak
directions: Brown steak, garlic salt and pepper on stove top.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then add onions and peppers on top.
Cover with gravy. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: eggplant parmesan soup
directions: Saute in soup pot in olive oil and margarine or butter the onion and garlic.
Skin and cube eggplants; add to onion and garlic; saute for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Then just cover mixture with water; let cook until eggplants are tender.
Add crushed tomatoes, basil and oregano; puree entire mixture in blender.
Return everything to soup pot; add Parmesan cheese. Adjust consistency of soup with added water, if needed.
It should be neither thin nor thick; cook over low heat for 1 hour, covered. Garnish with additional Parmesan cheese and parsley at table.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on plate or platter, then layer lettuce, tomatoes, black olives and cheese.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Melt the margarine; add flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together 1 cup Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup powdered sugar. Spread over crust.
Beat lemon pudding with milk until thick. Pour over mixture.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts to 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over top; refrigerate.

title: cream of tomato bisque
directions: Cook the tomatoes, sugar and onion fifteen minutes.
Press through colander, add soda and reheat.
Make a white sauce of the other ingredients.
Add tomatoes and remove from fire and serve at once.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all in bowl with electric mixer or use blender.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients listed.
Store in a well sealed container. Use 1/3 cup of mix for each cup of hot water.

title: wild rice
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 425 degrees, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt. Cook over high heat 5 minutes, stirring frequently, scraping bottom of pan until candy reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add pecans. Drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: plum cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer and beat until smooth.
Bake in lightly greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before turning cake out.

title: chicken-sausage gumbo
directions: Save all chicken fat.
Cut up sausage and hen and pan boil in Dutch oven until tender.
Remove all chicken from bones.
Save broth.
Make roux from chicken fat, cooking oil (if needed) and flour.
Make roux dark.
Combine roux, broth and vegetables.
Serve over rice.

title: orange slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add 4 cups cold water and 2 cans pineapple juice.

title: alaska salad
directions: Put prepared whipped topping in large bowl.
Sprinkle dry drink mix over topping; mix well.
Pour juice off pineapple, then add pineapple.
Do not use juice.
Add cottage cheese.
Mix well. Chill before using.
Serve on pound cake or eat with crackers.

title: savory ham
directions: Slice ham rather thin and blend all remaining ingredients. Place one slice of ham in a deep dish.
Cover with a spoonful of the seasoning and proceed in this way until all ingredients are used.
Set aside 2 hours to marinate.
Remove ham from dish and saute in a little margarine.
Heat the seasonings used to marinate in what butter remains in the pan and pour over the ham.
Serve very hot.

title: party pronto pups
directions: Mix all ingredients except for wieners.
Stick toothpicks in wieners, dip in batter and deep fry.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and boil for 10 minutes (drain).
Saute celery and onions in butter.
Layer potatoes in baking dish.
Pour soup, milk and sauteed vegetables over potatoes.
Layer Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick molasses cake
directions: Soften shortening and mix with sugar, eggs, molasses, spices and flour thoroughly.
Add hot coffee in which soda has been dissolved.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake in an oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse(diabetic recipe)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 2/3 cup into serving dish.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.
Two-thirds cup equals 1 starch and 1 fat.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix.
Fold all together until well mixed.
Spread on cooled cake and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake from scratch
directions: Cake: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar and pinch of salt in large bowl. In saucepan, bring to a boil 2 sticks margarine, water and 3 tablespoons cocoa. Pour over flour mixture. Mix well. Add to mixture the eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix the buttermilk with the soda. Add to mixture. Pour in greased pan (lightly). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reese's bits krispy treats
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Add marshmallows.
Cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir until chips are melted and mixture is well-blended.
Add cereal; stir until well-coated.

title: reese's tarts
directions: Cut cookie dough into 3/4-inch slices.
Cut each slice into quarters.
Roll into balls.
Place balls in ungreased mini-muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately press center of each cookie down with end of wooden spoon, forming a tart-like shell.
Place 1 Reese's into each tart shell.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix in vinegar, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: hash brown potato hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put crushed corn flakes and some of the Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn oven to broil; watch closely. Take the hot dish out after the top has slightly browned (about 2 minutes).

title: master cookies
directions: Roll Master Cookie dough very thin.
Cut in circles.
Put a small teaspoon of jam in center of one circle.
Cover with another circle and press edges together.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: polish coffee cake
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water and cool.
Let milk come to a boil; cool to lukewarm and pour into a bowl.
Crumble in yeast with 3 tablespoons sugar.
When yeast is dissolved, stir in 3 cups flour.
Mix together and let rise 1/2 hour away from draft or cold.

title: ham and cornmeal dumplings
directions: Cook ham bone and remove meat.
Reserve broth.
Mix meal, flour, egg and pepper.
Add broth from meat to make a stiff dough. Shape into balls (size of small egg).
Drop balls into hot broth. Cook, without stirring, until done.
Serve hot.
Chopped meat may be used on top.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cook chicken, using your favorite seasonings (poultry, garlic salt, onion, pepper).
Set aside to cool, draining broth into separate container.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill well and serve.
Easy and delicious!

title: fruity-baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In paper bag, combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Shake chicken a few pieces at a time in flour mixture.
Dip chicken skin side down in margarine.
Place in pan, skin side up.
Combine remaining ingredients except fruit.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce.
Pour drained fruit over chicken.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Continue baking until tender (15 to 20 minutes).

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water and salt until done (about 5 minutes).
Add to grits Cheddar cheese, butter, milk and eggs. Place in greased 2-quart casserole or glass Pyrex dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° until lightly browned and set, approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: monkey bread(don't preheat oven)
directions: Cut dinner rolls into quarters.
Toss in cinnamon and sugar. Drop into pan. Melt butter and mix in brown sugar.
Spoon over dinner rolls.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool 5 minutes and turn onto plate.

title: crock-pot pork spareribs
directions: Cut slab in to sections of 2 to 4 rib sections.
Season to taste.
I use Greek seasoning.
Place ribs into crock-pot.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar and barbecue sauce (optional) to make a thick paste.
Pour over ribs.
Cook on high 8 hours or so.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in the flour and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
(Cookies do not spread.)
Bake until set, but not brown, at 400°, about 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: boiled custard
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Mix egg yolks, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Then add a little hot milk to yolk mixture.
Then add to milk and boil until thickened.
Remove from heat and flavor with peppermint stick candy to your taste.

title: frosty pickles
directions: Place onion and cucumbers in bowl with salt and water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain but do not rinse.
Return to bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar and dill.
Stir occasionally and let stand until sugar dissolves.
Pack in freezer boxes, cover tightly and freeze.

title: betty's sausage-rice casserole
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with cheese and melt.

title: catsup
directions: Chop the tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Cook together and strain.
Then add vinegar, salt, sugar and spice to the juice. Cook down mixture half way and add cayenne pepper.
Dissolve cornstarch in vinegar and add to sauce.
This will thicken the sauce.
Place in jars and seal.
Yields 5 pints.

title: blue cheese bread
directions: Blend cheese and butter in processor until smooth.
Preheat broiler.
Broil bread, crust side up, until crisp.
Turn and broil, cut side until brown.
Spread cheese mixture over cut side of bread.
Sprinkle liberally with pepper.
Broil until cheese bubbles and begins to brown.
Remove from broiler and sprinkle bread with celery.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch pieces.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over cereal, coating well.
Pour into paper bag with powdered sugar and shake well.
Store in tight container.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In a bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening. Add milk and egg which has been beaten. Stir in cranberries.
Mix together.
Pour into greased bread pan. Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: it's-a-snap cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, mix Knox gelatine and sugar in boiling water, until dissolved.
With an electric mixer, beat cheese
into Knox gelatine mixture.
Pour into crust; chill until firm.
Top with fruit.

title: bake spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add green pepper, noodles, water and spaghetti sauce.
Stir in half the cheese.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with the other half of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture in and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash and clean beans and soak overnight.
Drain and add water, bouillon cubes, ham and pork.
Heat pepper, onions, celery and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add to soup and cook approximately 4 hours.
Add lemon juice and parsley.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: no bake coconut balls
directions: Cook until bubbly the chopped dates, sugar, butter and eggs. Mix Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla together until blended and add to cooked mixture above.
Then shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: delmonico potatoes(shortcut way)
directions: In heavy pot place frozen potatoes, cream, 1 stick butter or margarine and salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat until thick, approximately 20 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Place in 9 x 9-inch oven baking dish or casserole.
Sprinkle with plain bread crumbs and Romano cheese; drizzle 1/2 stick melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake until brown on top and bubbles up.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Place the ingredients in layers in large bowl.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat about ten minutes after adding all the sugar.
Fold in cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch layer cake pan or Pyrex pie dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in 325° preheated oven.
Chill.
Spread whipped cream on top.
Garnish with fruit, grated chocolate or coconut.
Freeze, if you like, before adding whipped cream.
Stays nice for weeks.

title: braised cabbage
directions: Heat oil and water in iron skillet until hot.
Add shredded cabbage, sprinkle with onion powder.
Stir often until tender. Chopped celery or bell pepper may be added.
Serve warm. Delicious with mashed potatoes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate to blend tastes.

title: pork chops ol
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a greased 13 x 9 casserole dish, combine rice, water, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Arrange pork chops over rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine together flour, brown sugar, margarine and pecans with a fork Until crumbly. Press into a lightly greased 9 X 13 X 2 inch pan. Bake at 375 for 15 minutes. cool in pan on wire rack. Beat Cool whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar on medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Put in pie crust. Mix water, sugar, cornstarch and blueberries together and cook until thick. Put on top of cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until set.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan liberally.
Toast bread and cut into cubes or use croutonettes.
Put in bottom of dish.
Add 2 cups cooked chicken.
Mix together the chopped onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Beat together the eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. The next day, spoon undiluted mushroom soup over casserole. Sprinkle cheese and almonds over.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a small hole, a medium hole and a large hole. In small hole, add vanilla.
In medium hole, add vinegar.
In large hole, add oil. Before mixing, cover with cold water.
Mix well and pour in ungreased 8 or 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana milkshake(kids' recipe)
directions: Peel banana and break into chunks.
Put chunks in bowl and mash with fork until lumps are gone.
Pour in milk and vanilla. Beat with eggbeater until shake is smooth and foamy.
Pour into glasses.
Serves 2.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Combine meat and onion.
Brown and drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco mix.
Place crushed tortilla chips in the bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with meat mixture, then top with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Pour juices and water into an 8-cup percolator.
Place the remaining ingredients in the percolator basket.
Perk for 10 minutes or until spices permeate.
Serve hot.

title: easy banana muffins
directions: Beat salad dressing and sugar into bananas.
Stir in flour, soda and salt just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minuets.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: harriet's breakfast special
directions: Butter long casserole dish.
Butter bread and lay facing down (8 slices).
Place cheese on bread.
Butter other eight slices and lay facing upward.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Fry bacon, drain, crumble and sprinkle on top of bread. Cover and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Place dish in large broiler pan filled with water.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour, until brown and puffy.

title: seafood au gratin supreme(charlie fetter's specialty)
directions: Brown bread crumbs in 2 tablespoons of butter; reserve.
Saute mushrooms in 4 tablespoons of butter; reserve.
Saute onion; blend together flour, milk, salt, mustard and add to onion, heating to boiling while stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat and stir in 1 cup shredded cheese and 1/4 cup wine.
Stir in scallops, shrimp, crab and mushrooms.
Place in large casserole; sprinkle with remaining cheese and top with sauteed bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until crumbs are browned.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.	Serve with chips.

title: oreo cake dessert
directions: Crumble part of Oreo cookies in bottom of glass dish.
Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour over cookies.
Mix instant pudding as directed on box.
Pour this over Cool Whip, then top with rest of Oreo cookies.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese with mayonnaise.
To this add 16 marshmallows, quartered or finer if you like.
Add bananas (sliced), fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Add green or red cherries for color.
Put in freezer and freeze.

title: better than robert redford(layered dessert)
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Mix and press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread this on crust.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Add oleo, oil and sugar together.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each egg.
Alternate a little flour, then a little milk until all is added, then add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325°.
Start in a cold oven and bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and cook sugar, Karo syrup, butter and salt until sugar melts.
Beat eggs until foam.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Combine with the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Wait until cool before cutting.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix all ingredients (except shells) and heat until bubbly. Fill each shell with 1 rounded tablespoonful filling and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (plus 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch, this extra dish may be frozen to use later).
Pour 1 quart spaghetti sauce over shells and bake until heated at 350°, for 30 minutes.

title: potato bread with sour cream and chives
directions: Add all ingredients listed in this order to your automatic bread making machine.
Select "white Bread" and push start.

title: venison stew
directions: Boil venison slowly, skimming off blood, for 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
Put venison and water in a slow cooker.
Add onion, celery, carrots, Worcestershire sauce, Italian seasoning, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cover venison and vegetables.
Cook on low to medium setting for 6 hours.
Boil diced potatoes until 3/4 cooked so they can be added with potato water to slow cooker at hour 5.
Cook on high setting for last hour.
Serve as is for soup, or add cornstarch to thicken for stew.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Add Karo, chopped pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into raw or frozen pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Combine all and mix with a mixer until blended
well.
Bake in glass baking dish at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: creamed chicken breast
directions: Boil chicken for 1/2 hour.
Debone and cut into small pieces. Melt stick of butter; mix with stuffing croutons.
Mix 2 cups of chicken broth (saved from boiled chicken) with seasoning package. Pour over croutons.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken in casserole, mixing lightly.
Put stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boiling in saucepan and add soup mix. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Stir in sugar, salt, cheese and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water in a large bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Stir in onion soup mixture and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 2 minutes.
Mix in remaining flour, a little at a time, with a spoon or hands until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and turn dough to grease top. Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and divide in half.
Cover for 10 minutes. Shape into 2 loaves.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Buy the pork tenderloin rolled and tied by your butcher. Bake it for 30 minutes on a rack in a 400° oven.
Make a sauce of the onions, butter, soy sauce, pepper, mustard and wine.
Remove the rack from the tenderloin pan and pour the sauce over the pork. Bake for another 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and baste again. Bake 30 minutes more.
You may need to double or triple the sauce, depending on how much meat you have.
The sauce will cook down and bake into the tenderloin.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in warm water in
large
mixing
bowl. Stir in milk, sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, egg
and 3 cups of flour.
Beat
until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make
dough
easy to handle.
Turn dough onto well-floured surface and
knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes. Place
in greased bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about
1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down and divide into halves. Roll
1 half into rectangle.
Spread with half of the cinnamon, sugar
and
margarine
or
butter
mixed
together. Reserve the other half of this mixture to spread over the last half
of
the dough.
Roll
up dough and pinch ends together. Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix 1st three ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Mix all other ingredients and add dressing and chill.

title: easy cranberry-orange sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine cornstarch with lemon peel, cloves and salt.
Stir in orange and lemon juice until smooth. Over high heat cook, stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Stir in cranberry sauce and heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 3 cups.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towel.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan and refrigerate covered overnight. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until set in the center. Leftovers reheat well in microwave.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Place chicken or turkey in a plastic bag, pour marinade in bag and marinate for 10 minutes at room temperature, turning bag occasionally.
Drain poultry, reserving marinade.
Place meat on the unheated rack of a broiler pan and broil 4 inches from heat for 4 minutes.
Brush with marinade, then turn over and broil 3 minutes more.
Brush with marinade and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Continue broiling for 1 to 2 minutes more or until poultry is tender and no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: many way butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo and powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Roll and cut on floured surface.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Dough may be refrigerated overnight for easier handling.

title: strawberry kiwi punch
directions: Add tea bags to Sprite; put bags right into bottle. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add the flour.
Mix together.
Add melted butter and mix.
Add corn syrup; mix.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 25 minutes or until firm on top.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Finely shred peel from 1 orange; reserve peel.
Squeeze juice from all oranges.
Measure 3/4 cup of juice; reserve remaining juice.
In a mixing bowl, combine the 3/4 cup orange juice, 1 teaspoon of the shredded peel, egg and oil.
In another bowl, stir together all dry ingredients.
Add orange juice mixture to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Turn batter into lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: baked imperial crab
directions: Fold crabmeat, after picking over for shells, into mixture of the other ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Bake in casserole dish in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 5 minutes at 425°, then reduce to 350° and continue to bake for 35 to 40 more minutes until set.
Do not overbake.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Using a pronged fork, cut butter into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture; set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together milk and sour cream until mixture is almost smooth.
Add the milk mixture to the flour mixture all at once.
Stir mixture with a wooden spoon until the dough stirs together.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Gently knead 8 to 10 times.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut dough into large diamonds or squares approximately 3-inches.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, leaving about 1-inch space between biscuits.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
10 biscuits.

title: chocolate ice cream brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool in pan.
Spread ice cream over brownies; freeze until hardened.
Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and pecans.
Cool.
Spread frosting over ice cream.
Freeze. Remove from freezer 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: pizza casserole #2
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine and line casserole dish with it.
Toss 1/2 of cooked spaghetti in melted butter.
Pour 1 1/2 cans of tomato sauce over it.
Add 1/2 pound pepperoni, 1/2 pound cooked hamburg with onions and 1/2 can grated cheese.
Add remaining spaghetti and repeat.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder in bowl.
Cut in cheese and butter with pastry blender.
Add water; mix well.
Press through a star plate from cookie press.
Bake on ungreased sheet in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Pour in the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat well.
Blend in vanilla, eggs and oatmeal.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost.

title: "stove top" rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, raisins, salt and 2 1/4 cups milk in saucepan over medium heat, 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Add margarine to hot pudding.
Combine sugar, eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Add to pudding, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thickens.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and spices.

title: swedish herring salad
directions: Cut herring into pieces; place in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining contents of herring, potatoes, apples and sweet pickles; blend.
Chill.
Add beets.
Place in serving bowl; garnish with egg, parsley and capers.
Yields 12 servings.

title: poor man's gravy
directions: In iron skillet, heat bacon drippings.
Add the flour, stirring constantly until brown.
Add salt, black pepper, eggs and milk. Stir constantly until thickened.
Serve on hot biscuits.

title: dollar saving carpet cleaner
directions: Mix well.
Use in any shampooer or with brush, using foam. Scrub carpet, let dry completely and vacuum.

title: oven barbecue brisket(must prepare ahead.  serves 8 to 10.)
directions: Sprinkle each side with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket and place in refrigerator overnight.
Turn once or twice.
When ready to bake, sprinkle salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce in same pan with all ingredients.
Cover and bake for 5 hours at 275°.
Add 6 ounces barbecue sauce and bake 1 more hour, uncovered.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 1 minute); set aside. Place remaining ingredients, except shrimp, in container of electric blender. Process until well mixed. Gradually add gelatin mixture; process until smooth. Stir shrimp into tuna mixture, if desired. Pour tuna mixture into an oiled 5 1/2-cup mold; chill until firm. Unmold mousse; serve with crackers. Yield:
5 1/2 cups.

title: ham in the can
directions: Punch 3 holes in top of canned ham; drain all water.

title: cream of po-cheesy soup
directions: While potatoes and onion are cooking, melt margarine in large Dutch oven.
Add chicken bouillon.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour.
Slowly add milk (use a wire whisk to dissolve lumps). When potatoes and onions are done, add to milk mixture (water included).
Add cheese, celery seed and diced ham.
Stir until cheese is melted and ham heated through.
Garnish with grated carrots.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In punch bowl, put 1 cake layer. Add half instant pudding, half the fruit cocktail, pineapple, pie filling, half the nuts, 1 container Cool Whip and 1 package coconut. Add second cake layer and repeat, ending with coconut. Chill.

title: capital chicken casserole
directions: About 1 3/4 hours before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken, a few pieces at a time, until browned on all sides, removing pieces as they brown to shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
In drippings in skillet, cook mushrooms and green onions until tender and lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to medium; gradually stir in undiluted cream of chicken soup, wine, milk, tarragon and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Drain artichoke hearts; add to chicken in casserole and pour mushroom mixture over all.
Bake casserole in 375° oven, uncovered, 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender, spooning liquid in casserole over chicken occasionally.
Skim fat if any.
Sprinkle with parsley to serve. Makes 4 servings.
Good!
Each serving:
About 585 calories, 35 g fat, 140 mg cholesterol, 780 mg sodium.

title: non alcoholic slush
directions: Mix all, put in freezer, stir once every hour until slushy. Or freeze solid and put in refrigerate the day before and stir. Serve with 7-UP.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a pan.
Add sugar, milk; stir until a full rolling boil stirring all the time.
Continue boiling 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and cream, vanilla.
Mix together until smooth putting into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: two egg cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 2 minutes. Bake in 2 layer pans or one sheet cake at 350° until barely brown and done in center.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute pepper,
onion
and
celery in 4 or 5 tablespoons oleo or butter;
add to cooked rice, along with soup, milk and broccoli.
Place
in
casserole and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: In a large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter and brown sugar until creamy.
With a fork, blend in flour until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remainder firmly and evenly over bottom of a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream oil, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add eggs, pumpkin and baking mix.
Blend well and mix in nuts. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake about 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack before slicing.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except eggs) in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Place eggs in large mouth jar and cover with hot mixture.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: peanutty crisscrosses
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour and soda in medium bowl.
In large bowl, beat butter, peanut butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork tines dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet, then transfer to cooling rack.

title: homemade barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook celery, green pepper and onions until tender.
Add to hamburger.
Add tomato soup and ketchup to taste.

title: honey biscuits
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer all
the	ingredients, except the corn chips in a greased casserole
dish.
Sprinkle	the
crushed corn chips on top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar, onion and salt; mix well.
Add very warm water and oil to flour mixture.
Mix by hand until almost smooth.
Stir in corn chips and enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter. Spread in a well-greased 10-inch pie pan, forming a ridge around the edge.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add mashed potatoes and slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Combine with syrup, milk, salt, vanilla and pecans.

title: no-crust german chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine over low heat. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: After cooking and draining hamburger with onions, add corn, vegetables, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in saucepan until bubbles.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and top with biscuits and then grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done (approximately 10 minutes).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sugar and mix well.
Add fruits.
If not smooth and creamy, add a little more pineapple juice.
Serve either thawed or frozen.
Make in bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and spoon into a buttered, greased casserole.
Combine last 4 ingredients and sprinkle over the casserole.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: sicilian style salmon
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in bottom of baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of stewed tomatoes on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, oregano, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Place salmon on top of potatoes.
Cover with tomatoes, cheese, oregano, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Wash tomatoes, but do not peel. Cut slice from top of each; scoop out centers and slightly salt insides.
