Mix tomato pulp, celery, onion, bread crumbs, salt and 1/2 of cheese. Fill tomato cavities with mixture. Cover with remaining cheese. Dot with butter. Place in greased muffin cups or greased baking dish. Bake about 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Remove bone from chicken; cut into small pieces. Place on bottom of 2-quart baking dish. Mix celery soup, mushroom soup, sour cream and almonds; spread on top of chicken. Then spread crushed crackers on top; add melted margarine. Sprinkle poppy seed on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Saute shrimp in butter seasoned with salt, white pepper and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Slowly heat cream and melt cheese. Thin with milk or cream if needed.
Add shrimp and serve over spaghetti.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well after each. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add and mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar (2 tablespoons sugar mixed with 2 tablespoons cinnamon).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes 2 inches apart at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in microwave until smooth.
Add pecans; drop on buttered platter by teaspoon to cool.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler until smooth.
Dip caramel clusters in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: chicken-broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli until 1/2 done.
Lay in bottom of large dish. Boil, strip and cut into large chunks the chicken.
Lay over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead and baked when desired.

title: cherry stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients, starting with pie filling.
Keep folding in order given each item until all are folded in and mixed together.
Chill.
Spoon out to serve.
Makes a tasty dessert.

title: heath crunch cake
directions: Mix devil's food cake as directed and bake.
Cool cake and then crumble.
Pour Kahlua over this.
Mix pudding with milk.
Place layer of cake crumbs in clear bowl and then layer of pudding and layer Cool Whip that has 4 broken Heath bars mixed in it.
Repeat layers and top with 6 broken Heath bars.
(Use a large container of Cool Whip.)
This is very pretty in a crystal pedestal bowl!!
And, delicious!

title: cowboy beans(to be cooked in crock-pot)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
In crock-pot, first put in beans (juice and all), then add pepper and onions on top of beans. Add hamburger meat, barbecue sauce and catsup.
Cook on low 2 hours, then on high 2 hours.
Do not stir until beans are done.

title: slush
directions: Mix in large pot; put in wide mouth container.
Freeze at least 6 hours.
Thaw for 15 minutes prior to serving.
Scoop into glasses.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of slow cooker.
Add whole chicken. Top with salt, pepper and liquid.
Sprinkle basil over top.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 3 1/2 to 5 hours, using 1 cup water).

title: dinner rolls
directions: Put Crisco, sugar and salt in bowl; add boiling water and mix. Let cool; add eggs.
Add flour alternately with yeast mixture. Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight, if desired.
Take out amount needed, roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Brush with melted butter.
Place on greased baking sheet and let rise 1 hour or longer.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown. Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: green pea salad
directions: Stir well all together and add mayonnaise, almost a cup full and stir all together.
Ready to serve.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Slightly beat eggs and milk together.
Add currants.
Set aside while you mix dry ingredients.

title: okra patties(yields 8 patties)
directions: Combine okra, onion, salt, pepper, water and egg; mix well. Combine flour, baking powder and corn meal; add to okra mixture and blend.
Drop by spoonfuls or form patties into hot fat and brown well on both sides.

title: fritos dip
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add onion soup mix, cocktail sauce and sour cream.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with Fritos chips.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook and drain vegetables and linguine.
Mix together. Combine remaining ingredients and heat, but do not boil.
Add to vegetable and linguine mixture.
Mix lightly and serve at once.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dark karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar thoroughly,
add syrup and mix well. Add salt and pecans.
Pour into
your
favorite
pie crust very gently.
Dot with butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: karen's venison pepper steak
directions: Boil venison in all of the ingredients.
Let boil about 10 minutes.
Cool and drain.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: easy pickled beets
directions: Drain beets.
Heat liquid with sugar, vinegar and cinnamon sticks.
Heat to boiling and pour over beets.
Cool; cover and refrigerate.

title: egg bread
directions: Add liquid ingredients to pan.
Add dry ingredients, except yeast to pan.
Tap pan to settle dry ingredients, then level ingredients, pushing some of the mixture into the corners.
Place butter into corners of pan.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add yeast.
Lock pan into bread maker.
Program for basic or basic rapid setting and desired color.
Do Not use timer because of the eggs.

title: milnot cheesecake
directions: Combine melted butter and graham crackers and mix well. Press one-half of graham cracker mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch greased baking dish.
Make lemon jello with one cup of hot water.
Let jello cool, but not gel.
Combine cream cheese, granulated sugar, and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Whip Milnot and combine with jello and cheese mixtures.
Mix well and pour over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle remaining graham crackers over the top of the cake and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving.

title: salmon stuffed tomatoes
directions: Drain salmon;
flake.
Mix with all ingredients, except tomatoes and
salt.
Cut centers from tomatoes;
salt insides. Fill with salmon
mixture. Broil 3 inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes until hot.

title: microwave orangey thighs
directions: Combine salt, (1/4 teaspoon pepper if desired), orange juice, honey, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Mix well and drizzle about half over chicken thighs in glass dish or pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 9 minutes.
Turn each piece of chicken, drizzle with remaining marinade.
Recover and microwave 5 minutes.
Cook additionally if necessary, but do not overcook.
Remove chicken from oven.
Drain juice in glass measuring cup.
Skim fat.
Add cornstarch to juice.
Stir well with fork.
Cook juice/cornstarch mixture in microwave on High 4 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over chicken or pass with ladle. Works well also on breast.
Adjust cooking time.

title: chocolate snickerdoodles
directions: Stir all together.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut. Roll in white
sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Make dark roux with flour and oil; cook until dark brown.
In a big pot, put meat and pour roux over.
Saute chopped vegetables in butter for almost 10 minutes.
Add to meat mixture, then add spices to taste.
Add enough water to cover mixture and cook for almost 4 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: vegetable potpourri(8 servings)
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in celery, carrots, onion and green beans; cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add a small amount of tomato juice if the mixture appears dry.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Mix and bake on cookie sheet with sides for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Stir the sugar and cocoa.
Beat all ingredients until foamy. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: white sauce for turkey tetrazzini
directions: *Note:
An additional 1/4 cup sherry can replace 1/2 cup broth if desired.

title: melt in your mouth dessert
directions: Melt margarine and while still hot, add flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding according to package directions; spread over cream cheese mixture and top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: homemade vegetable broth
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pressure cooker.
Lock on lid and bring to pressure over high heat, about 18 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 20 minutes. Remove from heat and let sit for 15 minutes to finish cooking.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Bake cake as directed on box. Cool completely. Crumble and set aside.
Drain pineapple. Put half the crumbled cake in bottom of a large bowl.
Layer in half the pudding, pie filling and pineapple until all gone. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, bouillon cube and seasoning.
Mix well. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Gradually add milk to flour, mixing until well blended. Add milk mixture to vegetables.
Cook until thick and add cheese. Stir until melted.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice; cut out stem portion top of pepper (carefully); clean out inside, washing out seeds with water.
Pot boil peppers 5 minutes; place upside-down to rinse and drain.
Saute onions, celery and chorizo.
Add spices.
Brown hamburg.
In separate pan, brown pork.
Drain grease and original mixture. Put mixture in bowl.
Remove with spoon or fork, don't take grease.
Add 1 mashed hard-boiled egg and 1 raw beaten egg.
Add cooked rice.
When peppers cool stuff gently.
Bake in casserole (greased with margarine, add little water), uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°. Can put pepper top back on like little hat.

title: festive broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: summer delight
directions: In blender at high speed, blend milk and strawberries 15 seconds until smooth.
Pour into 5 (12 ounce) glasses.
Add scoop of strawberry ice cream to each.
Slowly add soda or soft drink to fill almost to top.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add milk, margarine, eggs and vanilla to mixture. Cook on low or medium heat until thick. Pour into baked pie crust. Top with meringue. Brown in oven.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix onion and broccoli with cooked rice and Cheez Whiz.
Put buttered crumbs on top.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until well done, approximately 50 minutes.

title: sinful cinnamon butter
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer.
Will yield about 20 ounces.
Store in airtight container.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into desired size pieces; put in crock-pot.
Stir together soups and water;
pour over steak.
Cook on low all day or overnight.
Serve with or over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: baked rice and corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Place in baking pan and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crumbs are browned.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together and store in an airtight container. One-quarter cup of mix and hot water makes 1 cup of hot cocoa.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Dip in and enjoy!

title: flour tortillas
directions: Cut flour into shortening.
Add salt and baking powder.
Stir with fork until crumbly.
Add warm water.
Stir until soft.
Form in small balls.
Roll out to round circle.
Brown on griddle or in hot iron skillet.

title: quick and easy swiss steak
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In medium bowl, whisk together cornstarch and broth until smooth; set aside.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, heat half the oil.
Cook beef in 2 batches, until browned, stirring often.
Set beef aside.
Heat rest of oil.
Add onion, celery and garlic powder; cook over medium heat, until tender-crisp.
Pour off fat.
Add tomatoes.
Stir cornstarch mixture and add.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Return beef to pan; heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs and bananas. Mix well. Add flour, salt, baking soda with water to creamed mixture. Stir in vanilla. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50-60 min. Check with toothpick.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Melt butter; add peppers and onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add flour and milk, then crab meat, salt and nutmeg.
Cook 10 minutes. Pour in shallow buttered baking dish or use crab shells. Sprinkle with cheese, butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese is browned.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix in large bowl hamburger, ground sausage, bread crumbs, evaporated milk, onion, salt, pepper and allspice.
Mix well and form into 24 balls.
Roll these in flour.
Melt butter in skillet and brown meat balls slowly.
Add water; cover and simmer 10 minutes, then make gravy by mixing together in separate bowl: mushroom soup plus bouillon cubes for extra flavor.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pull from the bones.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup with part of broth.
Cover chicken with broth mix.
Saute onions with butter.
Add dressing to onion.
Add some of the broth.
Place on chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nettie's ladyfingers
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until very stiff.
Put aside. Beat egg yolks, sugar and anise at medium speed.
Fold in the egg whites. Fold in the flour and baking powder a little at a time. Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Each cookie is two teaspoonfuls of dough side by side.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar before baking.
Bake in 350° oven until edges are very light brown.
Do not overcook.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple snack squares
directions: In bowl, combine sugar, eggs and oil; mix well. Stir in flour and cinnamon (batter will be thick). Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden and a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool before cutting. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Cook sugar,
egg
yolks, Karo and flour until it begins to thicken.
Add
oleo and mix well.
Add pineapple and spread on cake.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Toss together the broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, red onion, and Cheddar cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Toss mayonnaise mixture with broccoli mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a bowl, cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in sifted and combined dry ingredients alternately, then the milk and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan (10 inches).
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour, or until a cake tester inserted in center of cake comes away clean.
Let cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: jam cake
directions: Add soda to buttermilk and set aside.
Cream margarine and eggs.
In separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture and mix with buttermilk.
Mix well and add jam, nuts and grape juice.
Mix well.
Makes 3 layers or 1 tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot crab dip(microwave)
directions: Blend all ingredients and microwave 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let dough rise.
Punch down and roll out to 15 x 17 inches. Then spread sliced pepperoni and shredded Mozzarella or Provolone cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook on top of stove until peppers are done on low heat, about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: plum pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs for 1 hour in 1 1/2 cups milk.
Cream together butter, sugar, egg, cinnamon and cloves.
Add soda to molasses and add to mixture.
Next add bread crumbs, raisins, prunes and nuts.
Fill paper baking cups and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:

title: tossed salad
directions: Combine and toss.
Add raw onion rings, mushrooms and croutons, if desired.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil slowly with crackers.
Stir thoroughly.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and sprinkle over crackers.
Stir well to coat crackers.
Heat in oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Better if made 24 hours ahead and reheated.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss in large bowl and serve.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese with yogurt.
Spread 1 cup meat sauce (ground beef and sauce) in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer one-third each noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella and repeat two times.

title: linguini salad
directions: Chop tomato and cucumber small.
Mix with cooked noodles.
Add Salad Supreme seasoning and 1/2 bottle of dressing.
Chill overnight.
Add second half of dressing, then serve.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat liquids together and add to dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 4 ingredients after measuring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well.
Roll into balls about like golf balls.
Roll ball in sugar and "smoosh" down with a fork or decorative cookie marker or bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned on edges.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Heat mushroom soup.
Add cream cheese, stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add gelatin. Mix in all other ingredients.
Chill.
Stir when semi-set to get a good mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Microwave chicken 9 to 10 minutes per pound (or cook in water).
Cut tortillas into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Chop onion.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add baking powder and cornmeal to flour.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper, onion and butter.
Add milk.
Blend well.
Combine gradually with dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Fry until golden.

title: peach jam bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat in a large mixing bowl the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add peach jam and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture; beat well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese and Ricotta; add eggs, sugar, cornstarch, flour, etc.
Last add sour cream.
Beat until smooth. Start in cold oven.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cake cool over or in oven for 2 hours.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in 2 cake layer pans and cool. Split into 4 layers.
Mix 2 pkg. fresh frozen coconut with sour cream and sugar.
Set aside 1/2 c. mixture for later use.
Spread the rest between the layers.
Mix 1/2 c. of mixture with cool whip. Spread on top and sides. Refrigerate in air tight container before cutting if you can wait.

title: pizza(makes 1 large)
directions: Let rise to double size and punch down.
Let rise again, then use.
Add pizza sauce, cheese and choice of toppings.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam fresh broccoli. Cut into small pieces.
Melt Velveeta cheese and milk. In casserole dish, place steamed broccoli. Pour melted cheese over.
Sprinkle Italian bread crumbs on top. Saute Ritz crackers (broken) up in butter. Sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sugar crisp cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and place in greased dish.
Chill in icebox until firm.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Measure sifted flour, cocoa and salt and sift together.
Add butter flavoring to cup of milk, then add milk slowly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fruity oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
In small saucepan, combine the apple juice concentrate and dates. Simmer until the dates are slightly softened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the butter, orange rind, orange juice and vanilla, stirring until the butter is melted.
Puree the mixture in a blender or food processor.
Transfer to a bowl; set aside to cool.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt in
top
of
double boiler the white chocolate and peanut butter.
Then pour onto a cookie sheet with sides, 10 x 15-inches. Melt in same double boiler the milk chocolate.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Place chicken into ungreased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Place slices of cheese on top of chicken.
Spread sauerkraut on top of first layer of cheese.
Put cheese over sauerkraut also.
Sprinkle on celery seed.
Pour dressing evenly on top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for one hour.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk and margarine until smooth.
Butter casserole dish and pour in
peaches then top with flour mixture. Place in oven and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: quickie cake
directions: Place a layer of canned coconut in the bottom of ungreased pan about 9 x 13-inches.
Over this, spread the canned fruit plus juice.
Top this with the yellow cake mix (dry) just as it comes out of the box.
Press down firmly.
Over this, cut 2 sticks of butter, distributing it evenly and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until evenly browned.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cube bread and layer one half in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish. Cut cream cheese in cubes; scatter on bread.
Cover with remaining bread.
Mix eggs, milk, syrup and butter.
Pour over bread cubes. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheeseburger chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Stir in potatoes, celery, onion, green peppers, bouillon, salt and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover and cook until veggies are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread sausage in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread over sausage. Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread. Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin. Beat until well blended.
Stir in flour, salt, cinnamon and soda. Blend well and put in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix together the
flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add the milk to
the
beaten
egg and stir in the dry ingredients, then stir in
the
bits
of apple.	Drop the batter into hot fat by	spoonfuls
and	let
fry until delicately browned. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with powdered sugar or jelly.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together butter, vanilla and sugar; knead well and add flour and nuts.
Mix.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll in sugar while hot and cold.
Then roll in sugar again.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sheila's spanish bullabesa
directions: Heat oil in a large pot and saute celery, onion, garlic, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook, stirring frequently, for about 15 minutes. Add tomatoes, clam juice, wine, parsley, fennel, salt and pepper; simmer for about 15 minutes.
Cut fish into chunks.
Add fish, shrimp and scallops to sauce and let cook for about 5 minutes until the flesh is opaque white and the seafood is cooked through as desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press on bottom and 1 1/2-inch up sides of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
In bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in sour cream.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until center is set. Turn off oven, leaving door slightly ajar.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; cool completely.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.
Remove sides of pan.
Top with favorite pie filling such as cherry, blueberry or pineapple.

title: tony's favorite vegetable squares
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Put on cooled crust.
Cut up tomatoes, green onions, green pepper and broccoli.
Place vegetables on crust; top with Cheddar cheese.

title: zesty cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces.
Combine bourbon, catsup, brown sugar, onion, oregano and rosemary if desired, in saucepan. Bring to simmering boil and add wieners.
Simmer until tender. Refrigerate overnight in sauce if possible.
Serve in chafing dish in hot sauce.
Yield:
4 dozen pieces.

title: m&m's party cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugars and shortening until light
and	fluffy.
Blend	in
eggs
and
vanilla.
Add combined flour,
baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of candies.
Drop
dough
by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie
sheet.
Press 2 or 3 additional candies into each cookie. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: won tons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray muffin tins with vegetable spray. Push a wrapper into each cup to form little bowls. Spray wrappers with vegetable oil. Bake for 5 minutes. Remove wrappers from tins. Mix all remaining ingredients. Fill each wrapper. Place on cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 50 won tons.

title: shrimp fajitas
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add shrimp, lime juice, oregano, cumin, green onion, garlic and ginger.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until shrimp are pink.
Divide shrimp mixture evenly among warmed flour tortillas.
Top with fresh salsa or guacamole.
Fold tortillas over from one side to other and enjoy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash, pepper, onion, celery, garlic salt, salt, oil and nutmeg with just enough water to cover and cook tender.
Do not drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Put in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and grate cheese on top.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: creamed turkey
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in broth and cream.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute; add turkey and pimento.
Continue cooking until meat is heated.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix together zucchini, soda, sugar, butter and beaten egg. Sift in flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt; stir to blend.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Fry chops in shortening.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole with lid.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, reserving the margarine.
Melt the margarine and pour over the mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° until bell pepper and onion are done.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix together and spoon into muffin pan (spray pan with Pam). Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cola roast
directions: Combine salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub over surface of roast.
Heat oil.
Brown roast on all sides.
Transfer to roasting pan.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Cover and roast 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: chicken dinner bars
directions: Melt marshmallows and 4 Tbsp. margarine.
Add Rice Krispies and press into 9 x 13 in. pan.
Cool.
Cook sugar, syrup, peanut butter, and 1/4 c. margarine until boiling point.
Cool completely and spread on base.
Melt chocolate chips and 2 Tbsp. margarine. Let cool and spread on top of squares.

title: truck and trash
directions: You may add anything that has an interesting shape.
Also peanuts and mixed salted nuts may be added.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Simmer garlic in skillet with oil. Add all ingredients to large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy and glossy, 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add eggs, beat until thick and pale lemon in color.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately; blend thoroughly after each addition.
Grease bottom of pan only.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let bread cool in pan 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato supreme
directions: Place tomatoes in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Saute celery, green peppers, onion and mushrooms in 1/2 stick of butter.
Place mixture over tomatoes. Add crushed crackers on top. Pour 1 stick melted butter over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion salt or 1 onion (chopped), parsley flakes, garlic salt and salt.
Let brown.
Add tomato sauce and Ragu spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour. Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.

title: my aunt mildred's fried chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and soak in salt water for at least one hour. Mix flour and Bisquick in a bag.
Put chicken in the bag and shake (a few pieces at a time).
Heat the Crisco to 325°.
Add chicken. Brown and salt the chicken on both sides.
Turn the heat down to 300°.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes, turning often.
If the chicken begins to stick to the frying pan, turn the heat up some.

title: dessert fondue
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate chips.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Put in bowl or fondue pot, surrounded by cubed angel food cake, pineapple chunks, strawberries, miniature marshmallows, mandarin oranges and banana slices to spear and dip.

title: grilled chicken fajitas
directions: Rub both sides of chicken with garlic. Place chicken, green pepper and onion slices on greased grill over medium hot coals. Grill 20 minutes or until cooked through, turning occasionally. Cut chicken and green pepper into thin strips. Spoon chicken mixture and 1/4 cup Velveeta in center of each tortilla. Fold. Serve with salsa. Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Whip cream.
Mix with all ingredients, except cake, then add cake and put in a large bowl and keep in refrigerator.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour into 1 gallon container and finish filling with water.

title: pastel mint dessert
directions: Put 1/2 crushed cookies into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip cream; fold in mints and marshmallows.
Carefully spread on cookie base. Top with rest of cookie crumbs. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.
The mints will dissolve into cream mixture.
This is scrumptious!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in water and cook until thick.
Take off heat and add jello.
Set aside to cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell, add cool mixture and refrigerate.

title: fluffy baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening and blend until mixture is like coarse corn meal.
Add cold 7-Up or Sprite.
Stir only until ingredients are evenly moistened.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 times quickly.
Roll to 3/4-inch thick.
Allow to rest for a few minutes.
Cut with a floured cookie or biscuit cutter.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; brush with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 flaky and wonderful biscuits!

title: popcorn cake
directions: *You may use 1 pound of either M&M's or Reese's pieces, instead of 1/2 pound of each.

title: deer roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot and cook until tender.
Then put in pan and cover with soup mix and mushroom soup.
Cook that in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crush cookies and spread
in
a Pyrex dish.
Cover with ice cream.
Pour syrup	over and cover with Cool Whip.	Freeze and serve.

title: bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs (unbeaten), one at a time.
Add flour all at once.
Beat well.
Add pure vanilla or lemon extract.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: easy chunky italian sauce
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan.
Add onion and pepper.
Fry until tender.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for at least 1 hour on low, stirring occasionally.
Then serve over noodles, any kind.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices 1/2-inch thick.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan overlapping slices.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cool.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix carrots, applesauce, vegetable oil, vanilla, eggs and granulated sugar together.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chicken pieces in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with dry stuffing mix.
Pour broth mixed with margarine over the chicken and stuffing.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Combine the remaining ingredients together.
Pour yam mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle coconut-pecan mixture over top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: creamed cabbage soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine broth, celery, cabbage, onion and carrot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk to flour mixture, stirring constantly. Gradually stir into vegetable mixture and add ham.
Heat through. Makes 8 to 10
servings.

title: corn for freezing
directions: Clean and wash corn on the cob.
Cut the corn off the cob. Measure out corn and add rest of the other ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Cool and then package and freeze.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Put cookies in blender and crush.
Add butter and blend well. Press into pie pan.
Whip the cream.
Mix marshmallow cream and creme de menthe (do not mix with whipping cream).
Fold marshmallow mix and whipped cream together. (Don't blend.)
Put in freezer.

title: grandma wagner's good old party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a hand mixer.
Serve cold. Hold the Brandy for a childs favorite.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: Sift together 2 cups sugar and flour.
Set aside.
In saucepan, bring to boil 1 stick margarine, oil, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour over sugar and flour; mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Pour into prepared 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake 18 minutes in 350° to 400° oven.

title: harold's frog legs
directions: Frying the frog legs is easy.
The job is getting them!
Once you've legally gotten enough for a mess, clean them, saving only the hind legs.
Soak in salt water overnight.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vinegar and all other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in pie shell at 250°.

title: my inexpensive but good rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Dissolve sugar and salt in the 3 cups hot water (from tap).
After sugar and salt are dissolved, let cool, then add yeast.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Add about 5 cups flour to make a batter.
Beat vigorously to incorporate air.
Now, add Crisco and mix until shine is gone. Add more flour and mix until batter doesn't take the flour.

title: sneaky squash pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar together; add egg. Sift flour, powder, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls; press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in rhubarb.
Top with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy pork chops
directions: Brown chops well in shortening in skillet.
Add onion near end of browning time.
Season chops with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Combine tomatoes, ketchup and oregano leaves; pour over chops. Cover and simmer for 55 to 60 minutes, basting occasionally, or until chops are tender.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream the oleo with sugar, beaten egg, seed and vanilla.
Slowly add flour mixture to the sugar and egg mixture.
Put in refrigerator and let sit overnight.
Pinch off dough and roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with wet or floured fork.
Bake about 12 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven.

title: microwave vanilla custard
directions: Combine the first two ingredients together in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture begins to boil.
Stir at 3 minute intervals.

title: hamburg squash casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Layer with sliced zucchini, then with meat, squash and meat again.
Sprinkle layers with onion and green pepper, also salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Spread top with bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Zucchini cooks quickly.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly and spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.

title: cherry-pink divinity(microwave)
directions: Grease an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart glass measure.
Microwave, uncovered, on High, stirring twice, 15 to 17 minutes, until syrup reaches a hard-ball stage or forms a hard but pliable ball when a small amount is dropped in cold water.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites in a medium-sized bowl until soft peaks form.
Gradually add gelatin, beating until whites are stiff and glossy.
While beating constantly, slowly pour the hot syrup into the egg-white mixture and continue to beat 6 to 8 minutes longer, until mixture is very thick.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in prepared dish. Let stand at room temperature until completely cool and set, about 4 hours or overnight.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat everything, except crust, together and put into uncooked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 325° until set, about 35 or 40 minutes.
Yields 1 pie.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix in order given. Pour into graham cracker or baked pie crusts. Chill 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mock sour cream pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix milk and yogurt.
Beat in eggs. Stir into dry ingredients.
Cook on medium hot griddle. Makes 12 medium size.

title: decorate with bread dough
directions: Mix ingredients and knead for 20 minutes, or to desired consistency.
Dough can be used in many creative ways.
Make ornaments by rolling dough out and cutting shapes with cookie cutters.
Make a hole in the top to hang with a piece of ribbon. Prick to prevent air bubbles.
Dampen to make pieces stick together.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.
Paint with acrylic paint, let dry and varnish.

title: tallerine
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add ground beef seasoned with salt and pepper.
While beef is cooking, add grated onions.
Sear beef until no red shows.
Add soup and corn.
Cook noodles; drain. Mix well with beef.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, oleo, shortening and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoon into balls. Lightly flour hands to keep dough from sticking.
Mix 3 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon in bowl.
Roll balls in mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Place pecan halves on a cookie sheet; pour melted margarine over pecans. Put in 250° oven for about 30 minutes; stir often. Melt chocolate bark; stir in pecans. Drop on wax paper. (I put newspaper under the wax paper to keep the wax paper from sticking to my table.)

title: carter salad
directions: Mix
fruits, peanuts and coconut and add orange blossom honey to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water; add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cranberries, orange and nuts.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with lettuce.

title: helga's molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, then egg.
Mix soda into flour, then mix in spices and salt. Add this to the shortening mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Fry bacon. Drain and crumble. Cook broccoli until tender. Let it cool. Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding mix over crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Top with final layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate several hours before frosting with milk chocolate frosting.

title: cream puffs - eclairs
directions: Add margarine to boiling water.
When margarine is melted, add the flour and salt together to the liquid mixture.
Stir, it will form into a ball.
Keep stirring and continue to cook for 2 minutes.
Take off stove and cool slightly, about 5 minutes.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating thoroughly between each one.

title: ham appetizers
directions: Work ham, bread, eggs and milk.
Roll into balls. Put in pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry sparkle
directions: Two quarts 7-Up may be used in place of sparkling water.

title: taco burgers
directions: Cook rice in water according to package directions.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in oil.
Beat eggs with pepper and taco sauce.
Stir in beans, tortillas, cheese, cooked rice and vegetables.
Shape into patties and place onto a hot oiled griddle. Cook until browned on each side, about 4 minutes per side.
Top each patty with 1 tablespoon sour cream, just before serving if desired.
Makes 7 patties.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Pre-cook green pepper cups in boiling, salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain.
(For crisp peppers, omit precooking.) Sprinkle inside with salt.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Brown chicken well in oil. Drain drippings, reserving 1 tablespoon. Saute onion, celery and garlic in drippings.
Stir in catsup and next 6 ingredients. Add chicken. Baste with sauce. Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes until tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Combine Karo, sugar, flour, vanilla, butter and salt.
Add slightly beaten eggs and mix well.
Stir in pecans and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour over tomatoes that have been cut in small wedges.

title: blackened chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Combine lemon juice, mustard, water and honey in a large bowl; stir well with a wire whisk.
Cover and chill.
Rub chicken with spicy seasoning.
Coat a large heavy skillet with cooking spray and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken.
Cook 7 minutes on each side or until chicken is done. Remove from skillet and allow chicken to cool.
Cut the chicken across the grain into thin slices and set aside.
Steam peas covered for 2 minutes.
Rinse under cold water; drain.
Add peas and lettuce to lemon juice mixture; toss.
Divide lettuce mixture among 4 salad bowls.
Top each serving with 1 cup tomato mixture and 1 sliced chicken breast half.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth. Cut fruit in size you like; any kind of fresh fruit.

title: crumb sugar cookies
directions: Measure and sift together into a bowl the flour and baking powder.
Add shortening.
Cut in using a pastry blender.
Then stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine and add sour milk and soda.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon or chill and roll for cut out cookies.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: dirt
directions: Grind Oreos.
Put a layer in a medium size flowerpot.
Combine margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Pour 1/3 of mixture over Oreos.
Alternate Oreos and mixture; end with a layer of Oreos.
Top with silk flowers and gummy worms.
Serve with a sand shovel.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the butter and crackers.
Put in a casserole dish.
Mix the butter and the crackers and spread on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, onion and sugar (3/4 cup).
Cook 1/4 cup sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over cabbage (do not stir).
Let marinate for at least a day or more.

title: crab casserole
directions: Heat milk and margarine.
Stir beaten eggs into heated milk. Stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add bread crumbs last.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° until top is brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream chicken
directions: Combine butter and flour in pan over medium heat.
Let cook until butter melts.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Serve over hot biscuits or rolls.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage balls
directions: Combine room temperature sausage and shredded cheese in large bowl.
Add Bisquick, a cup at a time; mix well.
Roll into 50 to 75 small balls.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Mix sugars, oleo and oil. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each one. Alternate adding flour and milk to mixture. Beat well. Pour into large greased and floured tube pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: golden cheese chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil in a Dutch oven; add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until vegetables are done.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook. Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir cheese mixture into vegetables.
Add ham and hot sauce to taste, stirring well.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Makes 12 servings.

title: j.c.'s baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Butterfly and leave tails on.
Crush crackers extra fine (like beach sand) in food processor.
Melt butter and slowly add to crushed crackers until it becomes stuffing consistency.
Add lemon juice, wine and dash of garlic powder.
Mix together.
Stuff shrimp.
Stand them around edge of foil pie plates.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with cups of melted butter for dipping.

title: egg-sausage quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; flute edges.
Do not prick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 minutes.
In skillet, cook sausage; drain well.
Sprinkle hard-cooked eggs in bottom of pie shell.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine beaten eggs, cream, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.
A 1976 recipe.

title: bacon cheddar appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread a generous amount of mixture on party rye slices.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until brown and bubbly.
If you prefer, you can broil rather than bake.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery slowly in skillet.
Add the rice, soup, water and soy sauce.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with chow mein noodles and almonds.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy italian toss
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine torn lettuce, the tomato wedges, cubed cheese, garbanzo beans, pepperoni slices and green onion.
Toss together.
Pour the Italian dressing over the salad. Toss again, being sure that the dressing evenly coats all pieces. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: roast hen with dressing
directions: Make 1 large cornmeal pancake with corn meal, soda, buttermilk, salt and egg; crumble.
Toast 4 slices of bread, then crumble. Also crumble 3-day old biscuits.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add celery, eggs, salt and pepper.
Chop eggs finely and then cook onions and celery.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Alternate layers of cake pieces, pudding and whipped topping, strawberries and bananas (sliced). Let your top layer be the pudding and whipped cream. Garnish with strawberry and banana slices.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Get out proper pan size.
Mix ingredients together.
Potato chips cover completed casserole.
Bake for about 30 minutes if noodles are hot, longer if noodles are cold.

title: red hot pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours.
Wash and cover pickles with water, ice and 1/4 cup salt for 3 hours. Drain and wash.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients in a small saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir pistachio pudding mix with crushed pineapple until completely dissolved.
Add whipped topping and stir.
Add marshmallows and stir; add pecans and stir.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Better if left overnight.

title: gregory's dump cake
directions: Spread fruit in bottom of pan with juice.
Spread dry cake mix on fruit; pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Top with coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together. You can add more vinegar if you like it tangy. It's better if you let set until sugar is dissolved.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Heat ingredients and form a sauce. Cut off flaps on wings. Dust each piece with flour and dip in heated sauce. Put wings on cookie sheet and broil until brown, then bake at 200° for 2 hours. (For 4 pounds chicken, triple sauce.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and milk 2 1/2 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and pour up.

title: diabetics fruit cookies
directions: Combine 1 cup water, oil, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine salt, soda and sweetener.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add eggs.
Stir into cool mixture.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well, then add nuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken and separate from bone.
Preheat oven to 350°. Empty package of broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup over broccoli.
Put chicken pieces on top of mushroom soup.
Pour second can of mushroom soup over chicken. Mix the shredded cheese with the mayonnaise or salad dressing, then put on top of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Slice margarine and put on top.
Bake 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Add all ingredients to saucepan.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: all american potato salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing, mustard and seasonings until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.

title: fish sauce piquante
directions: Saute onions in shortening until brown.
Add tomato paste. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add green pepper, celery and garlic.
Stir well; add water and cook very slowly for about an hour, stirring occasionally.
Add green onions, parsley and chunks of fish, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with additional chopped green onion.
"Real" Cajuns might add Tabasco.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Arrange in baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spoon cranberry sauce over this.
Mix oats, flour and brown sugar together.
Add butter and sprinkle over cranberry layer.
Bake 350° until apples are cooked through and top is lightly browned.
About 40 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix pie crust as directed on box and place in pie pan, spreading out evenly.
Peel, core and slice apples into thin pieces.
Place 1/2 the apples in the pie shell and cover with 3 tablespoons of butter, thinly sliced, and spread out evenly over apples.
Mix cake mix, sugar and cinnamon in bowl and pour approximately 1/3 of mixture on top of apples and butter already in pie pan.
Place remaining apples on top, covered with remaining 2/3 of sugar/cake mixture.
Cut up remaining 5 tablespoons of butter and distribute evenly on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: snickers ice cream
directions: Cut up 4 Snickers and melt in small amount of milk on medium heat or double boiler.
Combine eggs, sugar, Eagle Brand milk, cream, vanilla and melted Snickers.
Fill container to fill line with whole milk. Freeze in ice cream freezer using at least 2 1/2 cups rock salt to freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onions in rice.
Boil chicken until tender and cut into pieces.
Mix all the ingredients together using some of the chicken broth.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburg french bread
directions: Brown beef, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add crumbs from the bread, egg, mustard and cheese.
Mix well and fill the hollowed French bread.
Wrap in foil and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas holly candy
directions: Combine your marshmallows, food coloring, butter and vanilla in the top of a double boiler.
Heat over very hot water until mixture is melted, stirring frequently.
Remove from the stove; gradually start adding the cornflakes.
Drop them by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Decorate them with red candy pieces (red hot cinnamon).
Makes 36 pieces.

title: pork chop main dish
directions: Brown pork chops lightly.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush each chop with mustard.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all chops. Pour stewed tomatoes over chops.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: spicy applesauce cakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and spices.
Blend butter and applesauce.
Beat thoroughly at least 300 strokes.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat another 300 strokes. Fold in nuts.
Pour into layer cake pans and bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on the box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch pans.
Mix milk, sugar and marshmallow cream.
Cook over low heat until marshmallow cream melts.
Add coconut and mix well.
Spread on cake while still warm.
Then spread chocolate icing over the coconut mixture.

title: shepherd's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Hollow out center of bread.
Cut center bread into cubes.
Pour mixture into bread.
Place onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Dip with toasted cubes.

title: royal's famous peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain peaches well. Reserve 3/4 cup juice. Place peaches in 9 x 13 pan. Thoroughly mix cornstarch, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Heat reserved peach juice over low heat until boiling. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Pour mixture over peaches. Sift cake mix to remove lumps and sprinkle over peach mixture. Squeeze margarine all over cake mixture. Cook for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mum's mincemeat
directions: Use a large, heavy kettle or slow cooker that holds 8-10 quarts with room to stir.
Put sugar, raisins, molasses, spices and salt in kettle over low heat and stir.
Add ground meat, suet, apples and juice from apples (as you grind).
Stir after every addition and often during cooking;
6-8 hours of slow cooking should do.
Keeps a month or more in the fridge. Freeze or can.
Only juice from ground apples or a little hot water is acceptable for moistening; no cider or coffee allowed.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except cheese and barbecue sauce. Press half
into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place cheese on top. Spread
rest
of
meat over top, pressing around edge to seal cheese
in.
Pour
barbecue
sauce
on top.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: minute steaks
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large mixing bowl; add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle small amount of baking powder over meat and mix well.
Shape into oval patties about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Fry over medium heat until done, turning once.

title: fudge batter pudding
directions: In bowl, combine butter, 1/2 cup sugar and the vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add to butter mixture along with milk stirring until well blended.
Add nuts.
In shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish, combine rest of sugar, cocoa and salt and 1 2/3 cup boiling water. Drop batter by tablespoons into boiling mixture. Bake in moderate oven 350° about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.
Serve right from the baking dish and top with whipped cream if desired.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: Crumble first 5 ingredients together and place in 9 x 12-inch pan (save some for topping).
Cook next 5 ingredients until very thick.
Pour over crumbled mixture.
Put topping on.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and brown sugar well.

title: eggplant with mozzarella cheese
directions: Slice the eggplant and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside for about 1 hour.
Drain and pat dry.
Saute in olive oil; drain and place in baking dish.
Saute the onions and garlic in olive oil for 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, thyme and oregano; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour tomato sauce over the eggplant; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Slice the Mozzarella and arrange slices on top.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chunk cookie dough cheese pie
directions: Prepare Cookie Dough.
Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixer bowl, on medium speed of electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Pour into crust.

title: granola bars
directions: Toast oats
in ungreased, large shallow baking pan in a 350° oven
for about 15 minutes.
Melt margarine; beat egg and combine with
the
toasted
oats
and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into
a
greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put salt over cukes, onions and pepper and let stand 1 hour. Do not drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Put in any type of container except metal and cover.
Will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage, eggs and bread crumbs. Shape mixture into balls. Saute in frying pan until browned on all sides. Drain. Combine ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, and soy sauce. Put sausage balls in large pot, pour sauce over, simmer for 30 min. stirring occasionally. Serve hot. Can be made ahead and, refrigerated or frozen in sauce. Reheat to serve. Makes about a 100.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together the salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Add chicken and marinate for two to three hours.
Add remaining ingredients to the chicken and mix well.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in large casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, warm water and soup mix in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pack into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Top with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Add butter, cheese and eggs to hot spaghetti.
Form mixture into "crust" in 10-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High 2 minutes. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Set aside.
Microwave on High crumbled ground beef for 5 minutes; drain all fat.
Add onion and green pepper to ground beef in bowl; microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; microwave, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir.
Add this mixture to spaghetti crust covered with cheese.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until cheese melts.

title: food for angels
directions: Combine crackers, oleo and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks form. Spread over crumb base and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: broiled flounder
directions: Preheat broiler.
Arrange fillets on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with pepper, then brush them with oil.
Spread mustard evenly over fish.
Put fillets into broiler, about 3 inches from heat source. Broil for about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Do not overcook. Place on individual dishes; sprinkle with chives and add wedge of lime.
Serves 4.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Heat marinade thoroughly, add chicken and vegetables, if desired.
Marinate for several hours, stirring occasionally.
Use as kabobs or just grill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form all ingredients into a ball.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: banana-sour cream bread
directions: Slice bananas into blender.
Whir until pureed (1 cup).
Beat brown sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Beat in bananas, sour cream and vanilla until blended.

title: boudain dip
directions: Remove boudain from casing.
May use at room temperature or heat slightly.
Mix all ingredients together; season to taste. Serve with crackers.

title: best yet spinach dip
directions: Run hot water over spinach in bowl; drain, squeezing out excess water.
Thaw peas and carrots with hot water; drain. Quarter the radishes, then half each quarter.
Mix all these ingredients in a large bowl and sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Dump in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Put next 5 ingredients on top of mayonnaise and begin to stir into mayonnaise, stirring and mixing well.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Before serving, stir well again and put into serving bowl.
Surround with wheat thins, Triscuits, Ritz crackers, Melba rounds or Frito Scoops.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, egg, shortening and peanut butter together.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls, flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy cheese biscuits
directions: In a pan that would nestle the 10 biscuits, cover the bottom with milk, add the cheese, place the biscuits and back according to the biscuit directions.

title: crab hors d'oeuvre
directions: Separate muffins.
Mix and spread ingredients on muffins.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
Can be made and frozen up to 2 weeks before party.
Broil until brown.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt and brown sugar and cut in shortening until mixture resembles crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
To remainder add soda and cinnamon.
Then add egg and buttermilk. Stir until well blended. Turn into greased pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In skillet, cook bacon over medium heat.
Drain on paper towel.
Keep drippings; add beef and brown.
Drain.
Put bacon and beef in slow cooker.
Add broth, onion, carrot, butter, tomato paste, garlic, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours until tender.
Add mushrooms and wine (or broth).
Combine flour and water until smooth.
Stir into slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 30 - 45 minutes or until thickened.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over hot noodles.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: May substitute apple pie filling and spice cake mix.
Or may substitute can of drained pie cherries.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain all beans and put in large casserole.
Brown bacon and ham.
Add chopped onions; continue to brown.
Add mustard, ketchup, K. C. Masterpiece and brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Add this mixture to beans.
Stir together, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add eggs.
Blend until smooth. Add milk and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Cool.
Pour in pie shell.
Can be doubled.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine soy sauce, onion and garlic in the container of an electric blender; cover.
Process at high speed 1 minute or until mixture is very smooth.
Stir in gravy coloring and Beau Monde seasoning.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces, start early as this should take about 2 months, cover with brown sugar and cook over wood fire for 4 weeks, serves 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but only if necessary as most people do not like to find a hare in their stew.

title: hershey's cocoa cake(1st place in pa state greatest cocoa cake contest, 1994)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Dust pans with flour.
Place 4 ounces chopped chocolate in metal bowl. Pour boiling water over; stir until melted.
Set aside to cool. Finely grind 2 ounces chocolate in food processor.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Re-sift 2 times.
Using another bowl, beat sugar, butter and oil until well blended, approximately 4 minutes.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cooled chocolate mixture.
Beat 1 minute.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat on low speed until combined, about 1 minute.
Increase speed to medium and beat 4 minutes.
Add buttermilk, sour cream, vanilla and finely ground chocolate and mix on low speed 1 minute.
Spoon batter evenly between the three pans.
Divide remaining chocolate chips evenly; sprinkle over each pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, approximately 25 minutes.

title: lemon thyme potato garlic packet(serves 8)
directions: You will need 8 (12-inch) squares of parchment paper or aluminum foil for this recipe.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Tear chicken into strips; set aside.
Mix Ro-Tel, chicken soup, mushroom soup and chicken broth in a large bowl.
In casserole dish, place part of chicken, soup and Ro-Tel mixture. Put crushed Doritos chips on top.
Follow each step until pan is full.
Finish with crushed chips.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar, salt and water together; set aside for at least 5 minutes.
Mix together remaining dry ingredients; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest for about 5 minutes.

title: salad supreme
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add ingredients and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: strawberry-grapefruit drink
directions: Break up strawberries and put them in blender with one cup of juice.
Cover and blend on high speed about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Add remaining juice and blend until mixed.
Serve over ice.
Makes 4 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: skillet okra
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, add diced onions and peppers.
Cook until transparent.
Roll cut okra in cornmeal.
Add to skillet and brown.
Put sliced tomatoes on top and simmer 15 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and crumbled bacon on top.

title: cinchy macaroons
directions: Heavily grease a baking sheet.
Mix the 3 ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 40 macaroons.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown beef that has been cut into cubes in a little vegetable oil and onions.
Brown slightly.
Stir in the catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, paprika, salt, dry mustard and pepper and 3 cups of water.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken and serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer snowballs
directions: Soften ice cream; fold in cherries.
Place in freezer until firm.
Using ice cream scoop, scoop ice cream into dish of flaked coconut, coating all sides well.
Leave in freezer until ready to serve.

title: ribs, sauerkraut and dumplings
directions: Cut ribs into serving size portions.
Place ribs in 3-quart baking dish.
In bowl, combine sauerkraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Spoon over ribs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Beat egg and add milk.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir with a fork just until combined.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto hot sauerkraut and rib mixture.
Cover and return to oven for 20 minutes.
If desired, garnish with fresh parsley.

title: deer roast or shoulder
directions: Put all ingredients in cooking bag.
Cook until done at 250° to 300° all night.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix in a saucepan or double boiler, sugar, cornstarch, salt, water, milk, butter and egg yolks.
Boil until it thickens; then add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells and cover with meringue icing or whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cut meat up into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl, mix the following ingredients together: Veg-All, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and chicken.
Crumble up one sleeve of Ritz crackers and place on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the chicken mixture over the Ritz crackers.
Crumble up the remaining sleeve of Ritz crackers and put on top of the chicken mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in Dutch oven iron skillet until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue.

title: strawberry macaroon
directions: Combine cake mix, egg, water, shortening and 1 cup of coconut. Mix well (mixture will be very thick) and pat into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool whipped cream and fold in the strawberries.
Spread over the baked coconut mixture.
Top with remaining coconut.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil.
Mix well.
Insert wooden skewers in one end of each hot dog.
Coat with additional flour; dip into cornmeal mixture.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil, 375°, until brown.

title: round steak hot dish
directions: Brown floured round steak in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for
to	2
hours, or until vegetables are done.

title: baker's chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar.
Heat chocolate and 3 tablespoons milk until chocolate melts. Combine with cream cheese mixture and remaining milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell; refrigerate.
For a firmer pie, freeze.

title: quick chocolate sauce
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, mix together sugar, flour, cocoa, Butter Buds and hot water.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes in microwave until it boils and thickens.
Stir.
Add vanilla, milk and salt.
Cook another 2 to 3 minutes. Cover dish with waxed paper when cooking. Yields 2 cups sauce.

title: brenda's cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Thaw dough.
Stretch out to about 6 x 18-inch.
(Do not pound or over handle.)
Spread with a thin layer of butter.
Sprinkle on a thin layer of brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll longways and cut into pieces.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Bring water and spices to a boil.
Add tea and steep 3 minutes. Remove tea.
Add juices and sugar.
Simmer at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients and blend well. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together the first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in baking soda.
Stir in oatmeal and then remaining ingredients.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheets in about 1/4 cup measures.
You may need to form dough with your hands.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden.
Do not overbake.
Cool on racks.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Fold in cake (torn into pieces).
Add fruit to appropriate glaze and spread on top of other mixture.
Chill several hours.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix creamed butter, jam, sugar, peach preserves, strawberry preserves, apple butter and sorghum.
Add allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda to flour and sift into first mixture adding buttermilk, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Prepare vegetables; place in a serving bowl.
Stir together egg yolks, dry mustard, sugar, flour and butter.
Blend with vinegar and cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, beat in oil.
Thin with lemon juice if too thick; pour dressing over cabbage immediately.
Serve warm.

title: lentil pot pie
directions: Cook onion, carrots and celery in water with broth until about half done.
Add potatoes.
Brown flour in frying pan and blend with margarine.
Add 1 cup of hot liquid from vegetables.
Cook until thickened and combine with rest of vegetable mixture.
Add lentils, sage, parsley and salt.
Consistency should be thin. Place in a large casserole dish or baking pan and cover with pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pans with shortening and flour. Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 prepared pans.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes 5 small loaves.

title: old fashioned carrot pudding
directions: Mix all together and steam 3 hours.
Serve warm with lemon or rum sauce.

title: party beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off grease.
Stir in milk and cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden ham sandwiches
directions: Combine ham, relish and ketchup.
Spread between bread slices. Beat egg.
Add milk.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture.
Brown on both sides in butter or margarine.
Serve hot. Makes 4.

title: oregon applesauce cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream oil and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg, then applesauce.
In separate bowl mix flour, baking soda, salt and spices together.
Stir into creamed mixture, alternating with water.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
(Can be frozen without icing.)
Delicious with cream cheese icing.
This is an old family recipe.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix together rest of ingredients; add to dry ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased 10 X 15 pan.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cook on low until melted together or microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and continue to cook for 2 minutes, until melted and smooth.
Dip apples into warm caramel mixture.

title: chicken and tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Bone and dice chicken; set aside.
Saute onion, garlic and celery until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, broth, chicken and salt.
Bring sauce to a boil; reduce heat to simmer, loosely cover and cook for 1 hour.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Pour sauce over pasta, toss and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press rolls into ungreased 12-inch pizza pan to form crust. Spoon in sausage.
Sprinkle potatoes over sausage and top with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: texas chorizo
directions: Mix all ingredients, but the wine, with hands in a large bowl. Add wine as needed and continue to mix until all wine is used. Let sit refrigerated for at least 3 days before cooking.
The longer it sits, the better it tastes.
You may add onions to taste while cooking.

title: fried bananas
directions: This is a delicious way to use up a surplus of fresh or ripened bananas.
We have them for dessert, as a snack or even for breakfast.
Cut bananas lengthwise, right through skin.
Remove skin.
Fry on each side in a little bit of butter in a Teflon pan until brown and a little crusty.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Delicious!

title: quick and easy ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients and fill container of ice cream freezer.
Add enough milk and fresh fruit to fill container to "full" line.
Process according to ice cream freezer instructions.
Use strawberries, peaches, blueberries, pecans or any other available product.

title: stuffed potato dumplings
