directions: Combine grated raw potatoes with salt and hot mashed potatoes. Blend well.
Shape mixture into 10 balls.
In each ball make an indention and fill with minced pork.
Cover up hole.

title: mexicali pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable oil. Saute onion and pepper in skillet for 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, corn and marjoram. Raise heat. Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer. In same skillet, brown pork chops on top of vegetable mixture. Cover casserole and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic, salt and oregano. Stir to separate meat.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and noodles.
Place cheese around edges.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream of garden soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Place in 3-quart pan.
Cover potatoes with water.
Boil.
When potatoes are halfway done, add butter and veggies.
Cook until tender.
Add milk.
Cook about 15 minutes. Eat and enjoy.

title: corn and molasses muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flours, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal.
Make well in center. Beat together wet ingredients until blended.
Add corn kernels and cinnamon.
Stir to combine thoroughly.
Batter is stiff.

title: quickie fudge
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts and vanilla; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in greased dish and put in freezer for 30 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Keep in airtight container.

title: mom's biscuits
directions: Spray a baking pan. Cut Crisco into flour, adding milk as needed. Place about 1/2 cup of flour in a plate, spoon dough onto flour, shape with hands. Place in sprayed pan and bake at 425° until done.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Wash and drain berries, place in a medium size bowl.
Pour your dry jello mix over and make sure all of your berries are coated with it.
Let set a few minutes.
Add filling to berries and stir very well, so that all berries are covered.
Put this in refrigerator and let chill 2 to 3 hours for best results.
Serve with Cool Whip if you desire.

title: ramoki
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Roll chestnut in slice of bacon.
Pierce through with a round toothpick.
Bake on broiler pan for 25 to 35 minutes, or until done, at 350°.

title: fig jam
directions: Combine figs, sugar and strawberry jello in large pot.
Cook for 20 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
An electric beater helps to do the stirring.
Add Sure-Jell and cook for 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally by hand.
Pack in 6 pint jelly jars while mixture is hot.
Allow to cool slightly before putting lids on jars.

title: foolproof caramel icing
directions: Boil together the sugar, corn syrup and 1/3 cup milk until soft ball forms in cold water.
Blend Crisco with powdered sugar and hot milk; pour hot syrup over sugar mixture.
Beat until of spreading consistency.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together except onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Put onion rings on and brown.

title: butter yeast cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and yeast.
Blend in flour and chill.
Roll dough by teaspoonfuls into balls and flatten. Dip on one side into egg whites, then into chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes until slightly browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
If desired a diced apple or two with skin and a sliced banana or two may be added also.

title: new england salmon bake
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Stir in milk, salt, pepper and peas; stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Mix and bring to a boil. Drop in cucumbers and just drop them in until they are hot through and through.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Add milk and yeast.
Knead lightly.
Cut out and bake at 450° on greased sheet, or store in tight plastic container in refrigerator and use as needed for 1 to 1 1/2 weeks.

title: herb baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over top.
Cover and bake in slow oven, 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crescent chicken bake
directions: Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
Press 2 rectangles in bottom of ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake for 5 minutes until brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in apples, nuts, coconut and dates.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze while warm with your favorite glaze.
This cake keeps well refrigerated and gets better as time goes on.
Very moist.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients except cheese to boiling.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Cool and use blender to make smooth.
Keep refrigerated.
Instead of heating everything up, I sometimes half everything and use the blender.
You still need to add the cup of water at the end or it will be too thick.
This is as close to Pancho's old cheese dip as you will ever taste.

title: cajun devils
directions: Peel and halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks.
Set yolk aside and place 11 other yolks in a small bowl.
Coarsely mash yolks.
Add mayonnaise, barbecue sauce, relish, salt, black pepper and red pepper.
Stir well to combine.
Spoon yolk mixture into hollow egg whites, dividing evenly.
Press remaining yolk half through strainer or grate on fine side of cheese grater.
Sprinkle over eggs.
Top with parsley.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Thaw strawberries; add sugar and blend in blender.
Juice oranges and lemons.
Add 3 quarts water.
Seven-Up or Sprite may be added also if desired.
Makes approximately 6 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash
and
drain.
Add soup, sour cream, onion, carrot,
salt
and	pepper.
Melt butter and add stuffing mix. Put half
of
dressing	mix in baking dish, add squash mixture and top with rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summit meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl and set aside.
Combine egg, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Turn into a loaf pan.
Make a depression in the top of loaf and pour remaining tomato mixture over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cherry custard cake
directions: Tear the angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Press into an 11 x 7 baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the pudding mix, milk and light sour cream.
Beat until thickened, about 2 minutes. Spread over cake.
Spoon cherry pie filling evenly over the top of cake.
Chill thoroughly until serving time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: custard
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Set dish in pan of water.
Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, gelatin, salt and spices together in saucepan.
Add eggs, milk and pumpkin; blend well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Cool thoroughly.
Prepare topping mix according to package directions.
Fold into pumpkin mix.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until firm, 2 to 3 hours.

title: conference cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Ad eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Add vanilla.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Add oatmeal, cornflakes and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Fry sausage and put over bread in bottom of large baking dish. Chill overnight.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: surprise burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine beef, mustard, garlic, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and milk; mix lightly with fork. Divide mixture into fourths.
Mold meat mixture around Swiss cheese sticks, covering completely.
Arrange on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Heat rolls until crispy. Place burgers in rolls.
Garnish with lettuce and red peppers. Makes 4 servings.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Dough will be thick. Roll in balls.
Dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients until blended.
Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Add 1/2 cup pecan halves on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: white potato pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in cream, potatoes, sugar, vanilla and salt.
(If using leftover seasoned potatoes, omit salt.)
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: full-of-fudge bars
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, butter and eggs.
Press 2/3 of mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixed well.
Add milk and dissolved yeast.
Work together until flour is moist.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
(This dough will keep for a week.)
Pinch out dough; place in greased pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: shchi(russian cabbage soup)
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add the onion, leek and carrot. Saute until just beginning to get soft.
Pour in the beef stock and bring to boil.
Stir in the cabbage, sauerkraut and the tomato.
Cover and simmer for about 50 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Check for seasoning.
Serve hot with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkling of dill (fresh is best).
Serves 4 to 6. Best if made day before and refrigerated.

title: texas ranch-style gumbo
directions: Trim excess
fat
from	steak,	cut
into 1-inch cubes. Combine flour, thyme,
salt
and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour mixture.
Heat butter and oil in Dutch oven, add meat and cook until brown.
Remove
meat;
reserve
drippings in Dutch oven. Add onions
and
chopped
green
pepper;
saute until tender. Stir in meat and remaining ingredients except rice.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.	Serve over rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pasta salad con salami
directions: Bring 4 quarts water and the 1 Tbsp. salt to a boil. Cook pasta, drain well and immediately toss with dressing, set aside to cool for 30 minutes, tossing the pasta with the dressing occasionally. When cool, add the salami (be sure to separate the slices: they tend to stick together), peppers, olives, green onions, cheeses and parsley. Toss again until all ingredients are well coated with the dressing. Serve at room temperature. Makes 12 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender in 2 1/2 cups water, about 45 minutes.
Save broth.
When cooled, pull chicken from bone and cut into small pieces.
Mix together soups and sour cream; add chicken.
Put mixture into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with dry stuffing.
Pour 2 cups broth on top, being sure to cover all stuffing.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Combine egg and milk, beating well.
Stir together flour and salt.
Dredge mushrooms in flour mixture and dip in egg mixture. Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Deep fry in hot oil (350°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt. Serve immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn flakes together; place in greased shallow baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: world famous baked beans
directions: Cook bacon; set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings.
Put beans in casserole dish, add remaining ingredients, including onion and pepper, and mix well.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together with fork; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan (grease bottom only).

title: nana's gingerbread men
directions: Beat butter and sugar
until creamy.
Beat in molasses. Resift flour with next five ingredients.
Gradually add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
You may need
to work in last of flour with your hands.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick on greased cookie sheet.
Cut out gingerbread men and remove extra dough. Use raisins for eyes, nose and buttons.
Bake about 8 minutes or until springs back after pressing with finger.
Cool on rack.

title: honey dew biscuits
directions: Mix well all ingredients together and bake in greased and floured muffin pans.

title: radish canapes
directions: Mix all together and spread on different shaped bread cutouts: hearts for Valentine's Day, stars for Christmas, etc.
Keep covered and refrigerated until ready to serve the same day.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let set 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce; add to flour mixture.
Stir until moist.
(Batter will be lumpy).

title: nona's pecan cake
directions: Bake according to package directions and bake in three layers.

title: caramel corn(yields 10 servings)
directions: Place popped corn in a paper bag (grocery bag).
Add 1 1/2 cups of peanuts, if desired.
Combine all the other ingredients and microwave ingredients on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute, until it boils.
Microwave for 2 minutes more. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda.
Pour syrup mixture over popped corn and peanuts in bag.
Microwave for 1 minute; shake. Microwave another minute and shake.
Repeat once.
Pour onto cookie sheet and separate.
Cool.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine soups, Ro-Tel, seasonings and cheese.
Add Doritos.
Mix well.
Pour in a casserole and top with Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can be split into 2 casseroles and frozen.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg with strawberries and shortening.
Sift all dry ingredients into strawberry mixture and stir until just moistened.
Add chopped nuts.

title: sweet pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, until all flour has been absorbed.
Add more flour and knead dough lightly until easy to handle.
Roll out and cut into rounds.
Line pie pan with crust.
Fill with fruit and add crust strippings. Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 pies.

title: corn relish
directions: Place corn in Dutch oven; add enough cold water to cover.
Heat to boiling; boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Cut enough to measure 5 cups.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef in skillet; add green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add water, tomato paste and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 Parmesan cheese over bottom of pie crust.
Spread 1/2 of meat sauce, then sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella.
Layer remaining meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: low-fat broccoli slaw
directions: Mix together broccoli slaw mix and low-fat coleslaw dressing. Best if chilled before serving.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas, corn and beans and set aside.
Add pimentos, green onions, bell pepper and celery.
Mix everything together.

title: camping chicken
directions: For each person, wrap 1/2 chicken, onion, butter, salt and pepper in a generous sheet of aluminum foil.
Fasten ends and center of foil tightly.
Handle carefully and do not puncture foil.
Place in 350° oven or on campfire and bake for 45 minutes or more.
You may add potatoes and carrots to packet.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain well on paper towel.
Melt cheese in microwave or double boiler and combine all ingredients.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, then add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, glaze with Uncooked Chocolate Icing.

title: pasta in shrimp and wine sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter and olive oil in 2-quart saucepan until tender but not brown.
Add wine, instant bouillon, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes or until reduced by 2/3.
Add shrimp. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes or until done to taste.
Stir in tomatoes.
Add pasta and 1/4 cup melted butter; toss to mix well. Add cheese and parsley; toss to mix well.
May substitute 1 cup scallops for shrimp.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: charleston cheese dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top "baked" dip with bacon crumbs.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in angel food cake.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dirt pudding
directions: You will need silk flowers and a 6-inch terra cotta flowerpot.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes. Very easy, very rich, but very good.

title: grapefruit and cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar and mix well. Dice grapefruit sections.
Stir in cranberry mixture.
Chill. Makes 3 1/3 cups.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Mix rice, water and 2 cans soup in large pan.
Add chicken. Sprinkle top with Lipton onion soups and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
(Do not add salt.)

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Add undiluted soups and picante sauce.
Pour into chip lined casserole pan.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until cheese melts.

title: tuna salad
directions: Stir in mayonnaise to taste and 1/2 to 1 cup alfalfa sprouts.

title: hidden cherry ring cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Mix all ingredients except pie filling and powdered sugar with a fork; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spread 2 cups of batter in bottom of pan and 2 inches up sides and center.
Spoon pie filling evenly into center of batter and add remaining batter.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 8-inch pan. Make batter of all ingredients, except pie filling. Pour batter over oleo. Do not stir. Heat pie filling and pour over batter. Do not stir. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cocoa, flour, cornstarch and salt and bring to a boil until thickened.
Cool well.
Add vanilla and whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Place in a baked pie shell and place in refrigerator and cool well.
Serve with a few chopped walnuts on top.

title: pastel mint refrigerated dessert
directions: Put half of crushed cookies in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Whip the cream and add marshmallows and mints.
Spread over bottom layer.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate two days before serving.
The mints will melt into the rest of the ingredients.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Bring the sugar, milk and margarine to a rolling boil for 5 minutes, then remove from stove and add the oats, cocoa and almond. Put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan and place in refrigerator to harden.

title: quick 'n' nutty jam gems
directions: Freeze cookie dough 15 minutes. Heat oven to 350°. Cut cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices; cut each slice in half. Shape dough into balls; roll balls in peanuts. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

title: dietetic barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in water over low heat for about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cook an additional 2 to 4 minutes.
Good over chicken and steamed rice.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate with apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Combine remaining ingredients; spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil; add garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add clams with their juice and add remaining spices.
Bring to a simmer; pour over drained, cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Lemon juice is optional.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Power level Medium.
In medium bowl, combine chips and corn syrup.
Microwave at
Medium for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture can be stirred smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, stir until butter melts and mixture is blended.
Serve over ice cream or cake.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Place seeded grapes in pastry.
Combine sugar, flour and egg. Mix well.
Spread over grapes, dot with butter.
Seal above filling with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes at high speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat the eggs until lemon colored.
Melt the butter; stir in with the eggs.
Sift together the flour and sugar.
Add the flour and sugar to the eggs; beat well.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skins for 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Skin potatoes; mash with butter using a potato masher. Add along while mashing, sugar to taste.
Add salt, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add milk, a little along.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lentil nut loaf or patties
directions: Blend oats until fine and put in mixing bowl with chopped nuts or seeds.
Blend smooth remaining ingredients.
Mix all together. Let set for 10 minutes.
Place in Pammed loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or shape into patties and bake 30 minutes.
Turn patties over and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pineapple butter
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Place pineapple in blender and puree.
Set aside.
Place syrup in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced to 1 tablespoon. Remove from heat and stir in brandy.
Cool to room temperature. In a large bowl, beat butter until fluffy; gradually add sugar. Fold in pureed mixture.
Serve on any bread.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: lee county (s c) chicken pot pie
directions: Cook, debone and cut one whole chicken into bite-sized pieces. Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine cream of celery soup, onion soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Combine milk, flour and melted margarine.
Pour over other.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: california quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter until limp; set aside.
Beat eggs; add cream, flour, salt, paprika and pepper sauce; beat well.
Stir in ham or bacon, cheese and wine.
Cover; chill.
It is best to chill overnight.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: *Drain all juice and then rinse in cool water to keep salad from turning color.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer and pull off bone; set aside.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Press 1/2 of mixture in bottom of casserole dish; set aside.
Mix soups, broth and evaporated milk.
Heat. Place chicken over stuffing and pour soup mix over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown and bubbly, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in cold water.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes at room temperature.
Stir in ice cream; place in mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: golfball cookies(yield: a lot! can be easily divided in half.)
directions: 1. Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a skillet brown beef and onion.
Place the mixture in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add the vegetable next and cover with the mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° until warmed through and top is browned.

title: ham and broccoli royale
directions: Put rice in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Layer broccoli over rice.
Saute onion in butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk and cook until thick.
Add ham.
Pour into casserole. Layer cheese over ham.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and mix with 2 cups bread crumbs; sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: moulya
directions: Cook roast beef until very tender (3 to 4 hours).
Remove fat and pull apart into bite sized pieces.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 3 to 10 hours and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over raisin bread.

title: red and green christmas dish
directions: Cook sugar, tapioca, water, lemon juice and salt.
Cook together for about 7 minutes, until starts to thicken.
Cover and let set for 1/2 hour.
Add vanilla and a few drops of green food coloring.
Stir.
Cool and refrigerate, if not using right away. Will make 2 dishes.

title: grandma lyla's yummy dumplings
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into boiling chicken stock or soup that you want to add dumplings to.
They will fluff and rise to the surface when cooked.
In our family, the dumplings are set aside from the soup and flavored with butter, salt and pepper and eaten while soup is cooling.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Pour salt over squash and onions.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir next five ingredients together until sugar dissolves.
Add squash mixture and boil five minutes.
Seal at once.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice. Add drained fruits and nuts. Whip cream and fold in. Pour into mold and freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: (Sauce Mix):
Mix everything together except broccoli, onion and bacon.
Mix other ingredients and marinate for 6-7 hours.
Just before serving broccoli mixture, pour marinate over.

title: cheese chips
directions: Arrange on a plate with chips covered with cheese.
It is done when cheese is melted over chips.

title: okra goulash
directions: Cook
in skillet.
Keep stirred.
Add corn and tomatoes last. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add bacon chipped up.

title: seven up cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350°
for 25 - 30 minutes, makes 4 layers. Mix next 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat about 12 minutes or until thick, put between layers and on top.

title: easy sweet potato pie
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes, until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pierce bottom of thawed pie crust with fork.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 mins. Cool and serve.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix egg with water and dip chicken and coat with crumbs. Saute in 1/4 cup butter. Place in baking dish. Make sauce of soy, melted butter and chicken broth. Brush chicken with sauce and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, basting with remaining sauce occasionally.

title: easy chocolate cake(kid recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, combine the first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
Pour the lemon juice in one hole, the oil in the second and the vanilla in the third.
Pour the cold water over the top and mix thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes or until a fork inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost cake with your favorite frosting.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Combine cream cheese with a little cream (enough to soften). Add chopped nuts. Fill celery pieces with mixture. Chill before serving.

title: orange angel food(mrs. carmichael's recipe)
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until foamy, then add half of the sugar and beat again.
Add orange juice and grated rind.
Beat whites and add the cream of tartar.
Add rest of sugar to whites. Add yolks to whites and fold in flour.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a moderate oven.

title: rhubarb chiffon pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into single pie crust and bake at 375°
until done, about 1/2 hour.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and milk; mix.
Batter should be moist, but stiff.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling liquid.
Cover and cook for about 18 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen dumplings.

title: do-ahead breakfast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, bread crumbs and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in large casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Add milk.
Mix with rest of the ingredients. Pack in pan and let set for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crabmeat, 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs, eggs, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, scallions, Old Bay seasoning and mayonnaise.
Blend well, but gently, leaving the crab lumps as large as possible.
Shape the mixture into 10 equal portions. Shape each into a flat patty about 1 inch thick.
Coat each patty with remaining bread crumbs.
Chill until ready to cook.

title: iced pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs; add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Refrigerate dough until chilled.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip the balls in egg whites and roll in the crushed pecans.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and smash center of ball with thumb, leaving a bowl shape.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
The cooled cookies can be iced with a favorite icing or filled with fruit jam.

title: six week raisin muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, oil and milk and mix well.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Rest of batter may be stored in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Put carrots, onion and green peppers in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and boil for 5 minutes; pour over carrot mix.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
May be stored for weeks.

title: chinese salad
directions: Break up noodles and brown in 1/2 stick oleo.
Drain noodles on paper towel.
Brown chicken on all sides until cooked through.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: shrimp and crabmeat mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in lemon juice and water.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Transfer to 15 individual salad or gelatin molds and chill until firm.

title: chocolate mint silk pie
directions: In small mixer bowl combine sugar and butter.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed.
Add chocolate and peppermint extract, continue beating until well mixed.
Add eggs and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Spoon into ready-made crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream.

title: helen's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo syrup and water until it starts bubbling, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add peanuts after it has cooked.
Add salt, butter and soda.
(Can add vanilla or coconut, if desired.)
Spread foil on a cookie sheet and butter it.
Pour candy on foil.
Candy will turn brittle in cold water when done.

title: chicken with sausage stew
directions: Shake chicken in flour mixture, saute in oil until golden brown in a frying pan.
Remove chicken.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions, celery, green peppers and carrots in butter.
When tender, add broth, rice and meat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese and milk.
Stir until well blended.
Cook on low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Just before serving, add the almonds.
Garnish with minced parsley or chives, if desired.

title: texas chili
directions: Heat a large, heavy bottomed pot for 3 to 5 minutes with nothing in it.
Add ground beef and brown completely, breaking up meat as it browns.
(Note:
If using beef cubes, add 1/4 cup vegetable oil first.)
When meat is completely browned, add in the onion, peppers, garlic salt and pepper and cook until vegetables are wilted.
(Do not drain off grease at this time as it adds flavor.)
When vegetables are wilted, add in all remaining spices, the diced chilies and jalapenos.
Cook and stir for about 8 to 10 more minutes.
Add diced tomatoes and kidney beans and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: "lemon pops"
directions: You will need small cups and craft sticks.
Prepare lemonade and pour into cups.
Place craft sticks in cups and place on tray in freezer until hardened.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Stir into milk and eggs.
Mix cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour into egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick and leaves holes as it bubbles.
Stir constantly or it will stick.
When thick, remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue.

title: coconut cream pies(makes three)
directions: Mix beaten eggs, milk, sugar and flour together; cook slowly until thickens.
Add coconut, oleo and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Save egg whites if desired, beaten.
Pour over filling; sprinkle with coconut and brown.

title: pul go gee korean style
directions: Combine all ingredients; marinate at least 1/2 hour.
Cook on a hot grill for 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Serve on a bed of rice with vegetables on side.
May use broiler instead.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the water.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Chill until partially set, then whip until foamy.
Fold in dessert topping.

title: peach meringues
directions: Place peaches in a 9-inch pie plate.
Fill center of each with 1 teaspoon jelly.
Sprinkle with brandy.
Set aside.
Beat eggs in small bowl to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff, but not dry, peaks form.
Beat in almond extract.
Spread equal amounts of meringue over each peach, twirling to make a decorative swirl.
Bake in preheated oven at
425° for 10 minutes, until lightly golden.
Makes 4 servings.
Each contains 159 calories, 3 protein, 15 g fat, 37 carb., 30 mg sodium and 0 cholesterol. Exchanges: 2 1/2 fruit, 1/4 lean meat.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Heat milk and margarine (melt).
Pour over sugar and salt. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
When milk is cool, add yeast. Add flour to make stiff batter.
Let rise.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini fritter
directions: Make the Red Pepper Mayonnaise.
Set aside.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add the bananas and cream again.
Add the eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda and baking powder.
Alternately add the flour mixture to the banana mixture, mixing well.
Add the sour milk and stir until well blended.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Into large sized mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and hot water.
Add bread and let stand until mixture is lukewarm.
Stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Put casserole into a shallow pan.
Fill pan with hot water to depth of 1-inch.
Bake in 350° moderate oven until a sharp bladed knife inserted near center of pudding comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve hot or chilled with jelly or fruit or cream.

title: rio grande quesadillas
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, taco spices and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Stir in refried beans.
On 1/2 side of each tortilla, spread approximately 1/3 cup of chicken-bean mixture.
Layer cheese, pimiento, green onions and cilantro on top of each tortilla.
Fold each in half.
In large skillet, heat a small amount of oil and quickly fry folded tortilla on each side until slightly crisp. Repeat
with each folded tortilla.
Cut each quesadilla in quarters and serve with chunky salsa and guacamole.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in a pan with 1/2 cup water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Reserve broth and water to make 1 cup.
Mix with soup, chili salsa and milk.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Arrange 1/2 tortillas in buttered dish.
Top with 1/2 chicken (bite size pieces).
Repeat tortillas and chicken and pour soup mixture over all.
Top with onion and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
(You can omit refrigeration.) Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: "Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you; and as I gave you the green plants, I give you everything."
Genesis 9:3

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and beat about 2 minutes, or until oranges become pulp. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or one 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
While cake is baking, make the icing.

title: apple squares
directions: Make 2 double pie crust recipes.
Line an oblong shallow pan with half of the crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour together and sprinkle over bottom crust.
Peel apples; slice and arrange on top of sugar and flour mixture.
Mix another 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour together and sprinkle over top of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with salt, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining half of dough for top crust.
Cut a few slits for steam to escape.
Lay over apples.
Moisten edge of pie crust; turn under and flute.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost lightly while warm with powdered sugar frosting. Cut in squares when cool.

title: summer vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and squash; saute until tender-crisp, 5 minutes.
Set aside. Flute edges of pie crust.
Place pie plate on baking sheet. Sprinkle cheese over bottom of crust.
Spoon onion and squash over cheese; set aside.
In medium bowl, whisk eggs with 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon of pepper and the half and half just until mixed, not frothy.
Pour mixture into prepared pie crust.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Bake quiche on lower rack of oven for 50 minutes or until custard is puffy and set in center.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut with apples
directions: Drain the sauerkraut.
Saute onion slices in butter in saucepan.
Quarter and core apple; cut into thin slices.
Add to the onion.
Saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add drained sauerkraut and brown sugar; mix gently.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: (fruit) crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend in butter; work with fingers to make crumbly.

title: peach pie dessert
directions: Mix everything together by hand, except peaches.
Make double pie crusts.
Line 9-inch pie pan with crust.
Peel and slice peaches into pan.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Make lattice top crust or put whole crust over top of pie.
Poke holes in a solid crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 7 minutes.
Add margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and chopped nuts if desired.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
When totally set, cut into squares.

title: crocked vegetables
directions: Combine all vegetables and put into crock-pot.
Layer with butter.
Cook on high for 3 hours or until potatoes are soft. Stir 2 times while cooking and just before serving.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and milk together well.
Mix together flour, sugar and nutmeg; add to egg mixture.
Stir in cut rhubarb.
Pour into pastry.
Dot with oleo.
Cover with lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients starting with liquids and adding dry. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until middle springs back when tested.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and salt in water.
Co not drain when done.
In a large skillet melt margarine, add onion and broccoli, cook slowly until tender.
Add cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Stir in rice mixture and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Combine eggs with unsweetened applesauce.
Then combine baking soda and boiling water.
Sift together flour, salt cinnamon, allspice and powdered cloves.
Combine all mixtures and beat well to blend.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350 F.
Cool completely.
Wrap tightly with plastic wrap and store in a cool dry place for up to 3 weeks. Can be moistened with brandy or wine.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add baking powder, soda and salt; beat.
Add flour and beat.
Add oatmeal and beat.
Add coconut and beat.
Add candied orange slices and mix. Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 3-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Saut onions and pepper in oleo. Add meat and cook until gray, not brown. Keep from lumping. Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and Fritos. Mix well with salt and pepper to taste. Put in large casserole and cover entirely with a very thick layer of grated cheese. Top with crushed Fritos. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Serves a lot.

title: baked country ham slices
directions: Place sliced ham in pan.
Pour pineapple juice over it and sprinkle with brown sugar (amount of brown sugar depends upon how sweet you want the ham to taste).
Bake for 2 hours at 325°. Cover for the first hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving a little (3 to 4 tsp.) cherry juice for dressing.
Mix together pineapple chunks and cherries. Blend together sour cream and a little cherry juice to taste for dressing.
Fold oranges and dressing into pineapple and cherries. Cover and refrigerate.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: fish and shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp.
Combine water, onion and condiments in 3 to 4 quart casserole.
Wrap fish in double cheesecloth.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Simmer on low 8 to 10 minutes (save broth).
Cut up shrimp; flake fish.
Add veggies.
Beat lemon juice and oil. Stirring constantly, add 2/3 cup of broth, tomato paste and pepper. Toss and let marinate for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 first course servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour 1/2 of melted margarine into a mixing bowl and pour remaining margarine into bread pan.
Add remaining ingredients to melted margarine and add enough buttermilk to mixture to blend and mix well.
Pour into bread pan and cook until golden brown.

title: rum cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar while beating.
Soak 1 tablespoon gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Put gelatin and water over low heat; let come to boil.
When gelatin is dissolved, pour over egg mixture, stirring briskly.
Whip 1 pint heavy cream until stiff.
Fold into egg mixture and add the 1/2 cup rum.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust. Decorate with chocolate curls.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine shortening, sugar and lemon rind until creamy.
Beat in eggs and bananas.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add sifted ingredients in 3 parts to sugar mixture.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Fold in 1/2 cup broken walnuts.
Place batter in greased pans.
Bake about 1 hour or until done.
Cool before serving.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk in a bowl.
Stir in pineapple.
Pour into ice cream container.
Finish filling with Orange Crush. Follow instructions on ice cream freezer.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and egg yolks and beat. Sift flour and soda; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350°.

title: no fuss onion soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microdish, combine onion, broth, water, Worcestershire and garlic powder.
Microcook covered on 100% power for 8 to 10 minutes or until onions are tender and mixture is boiling over the entire surface.
Stir twice.
Pass the croutons. Makes 3 servings.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo.
Add peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Frost, cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, place butter, sugar, nutmeg and blueberries.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Combine lemon juice and cornstarch.
Stir into blueberry mixture.
Continue to cook and stir until thickened.
Serve warm over waffles or pancakes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: roast meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs with salt, pepper, thyme, nutmeg and cloves until well mixed.
Stir in milk, sour cream and bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes to permit bread crumbs to absorb moisture.
Add beef, pork, veal, onions, parsley, celery leaves, chives and garlic; mix lightly until well blended. Turn mixture into large, shallow baking pan.
Moisten hands with water and shape meat mixture into loaf about 8 x 3 x 2 1/2-inches. Place bacon strips over top.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs alternately with flour and salt to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: catalina salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add dressing just before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar until blended.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Make into 1/2 inch balls.
Melt chocolate; dip balls and let cool on wax paper.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over all ingredients except bacon and nuts.
Add these just before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy, then add flour, making sure that dough is not too dry.
Roll into balls about 1 1/2-inches. Roll in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add carrots; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce flame.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and 1 cup water over medium heat; bring to boil. Reduce heat and cook an additional 6 minutes.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and flavoring.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 more minutes. Add dry gelatin; mix well.
Pour into prepared jelly jars.

title: cream cheese dill dip
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
(For thinner dip, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.)
Serve with potato chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape in round ball.
Roll in chopped pecan or you may roll in 1 package of dried beef (cut up fine).

title: strawberry torte
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix with sugar and oleo and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Mix in a very large bowl the egg whites, sugar, salt, lemon juice, strawberries and juice.
Mix at top speed for 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and pudding mixes; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute. Stir in whipped topping until smooth and well blended. Spread 2 tablespoons jam on crust. Spoon cream cheese mixture on top. Top with red raspberries. Garnish with white chocolate curls made from Baker's chocolate or thick chocolate syrup.

title: cherry pie
directions: Put cherry pie filling in 10-inch pie pan.
Cut bread in slices and put over filling.
Melt butter and mix sugar, egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring all together. Pour over pie.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix real well and pour into pie shell. Cook real, real slow until it is dark golden brown.

title: dirt
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and cream cheese.
In separate bowl, beat pudding and milk until thick, approximately 1 to 2 minutes.
Add pudding to butter and cream cheese mixture. Combine well; fold in whipping cream and continue to beat for additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Butter a flowerpot!
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Layer mixture, leaving dirt on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay slightly browned chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, Miracle Whip and lemon juice together and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Mix Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs with melted butter.
Spread on spoon on top.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry-pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly with cooking oil.
Slowly add sugar.
Sift and combine flour, soda and spices.
Mix with egg mixture.
Add canned pumpkin and blend in.
Fold in chopped cranberries.
Grease 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch, and bake for approximately 40 minutes at 350°.
You may wish to top with vanilla icing.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash the apples and cut into quarters, leaving in skins and seeds.
Cover with water or fresh apple cider and simmer until fruit is reduced to a soft pulp.
Press the fruit through a sieve or food mill to get pulp and juice. Discard the skins and seeds. Measure the pulp and add sugar and spices.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until the mixture is very thick and has a nice, deep, reddish color.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes about 2 1/2 pints.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add water to raisins.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add raisin mixture and nuts.
On greased cookie sheet place dough by tablespoon, well apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: viennese torte
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, margarine and water.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Line 2 (10 1/2 x 15-inch) cookie sheets with oiled waxed paper.
Divide batter evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut each sheet lengthwise into 3 strips.
Assemble with your favorite chocolate frosting between strips and on top.
Frost sides with whipped topping and sprinkle sides with nuts.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare one cake mix in 13 x 9-inch pan.
When done, pour creme of coconut over cake.
(Retain 1 tablespoon for icing.) Cool cake.
Combine all icing ingredients and top with coconut. Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: your own curry
directions: Place all ingredients in shallow baking pan in 200° oven for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place mix in blender and blend until well ground.
Package in 1/4-cup portions.
Makes 3.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix, chill and serve.
Use whatever color Kool-Aid to match color scheme.

title: "grandma stella's" no bake apple stack cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix applesauce and cinnamon.
Place graham cracker squares in bottom of dish.
Cover with applesauce.
Repeat until desired height.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: orange cappuccino cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Heat chocolate and water over low heat, stirring until melted. Stir in coffee mix and orange peel.
Set aside to cool slightly.

title: three-bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and peas according to package directions.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients except crumbs and mix together.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: avocado and tomato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce; pour over avocados.
Toss.
Stir in bacon, tomatoes and onion.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Serve on salad greens.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 425°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
first
ingredients
in
saucepan; mix well. Simmer while
stirring frequently.
Blend butter (melted) and flour in a
small bowl.
Stir into corn mixture and mix well. Pour into
1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until bubbly and brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beverage barn pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil for a few minutes.
Important to boil for a few minutes.
Pour over eggs in a jar.
Cool and put lid on.
The longer they sit the better they are.

title: peanut butter bonbon
directions: Mix powdered sugar, butter and peanut butter together. Shape into bite size balls. Melt paraffin in double boiler. Add butterscotch or chocolate chips. Dip balls in butterscotch. Then place on waxed paper until firm.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Beat eggs together well and add brown sugar. Then add cold water and vanilla; beat. Sift flour and soda together and add to the first mixture. Lastly, add orange slices and nuts. Bake in moderate oven in oblong pan. Cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix together the tomatoes, grated potato, butter and water. Cook and stir over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until butter melts and the potato begins to thicken the tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in the soda which prevents curdling, then add the milk.
Add the grated onion.
Stir over low heat and cook to desired temperature.

title: chicago barbecue
directions: Chop and fry separate.
Put together and add 1 bottle chili sauce (Heinz) and 1 bottle water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer.
Thicken with oatmeal (about 1/2 cup).

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells until "al dente" or according to package instructions; drain and set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, spinach, 3/4 pound of Mozzarella cheese, salt and pepper together.
Stuff mixture in shells and put them in open glass baking dish.
Grease dish.
Cook ground beef (pouring off grease); mix with spaghetti sauce.
Pour this mix over shells.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and brown for 5 more minutes.

title: bonbons
directions: In large bowl, mix well together butter, powdered sugar, condensed milk, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Roll into bite sized balls.
Chill well.
Dip balls into melted paraffin and chocolate chips.
Place on wax paper.

title: chalupas
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In crock-pot, simmer beans for 6 hours with roast on top.
Shred pork roast into beans, discarding fat and bones..
Add spices.
Stir.
Serve on flour tortillas with shredded cheese and salsa.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic in heavy 4-quart saucepan, stirring until ground beef is crumbly.
Drain. Stir in soup, undrained beans, vinegar and chili powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring mixture. Ladle into serving bowls.
Top with sour cream and green onions. Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in egg yolks.
Boil 1 more minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue on top of pie.
Bake until brown at 400° (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool to room temperature.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef; add taco mix and water.
Simmer until thickened, 10 minutes or so.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter/margarine. Add flour, salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato sauce. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Add shrimp last 10 minutes.

title: spring pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook pasta in stockpot according to package directions; drain in large colander. Return pasta to stockpot; keep warm.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Saute onion with butter, salt, dill weed and oregano; add flour until thickened.
Add broth and stir until smooth.
Add in milk.
Stir in chopped spinach.
Pour some mixture on bottom of baking pan.
Place chicken breasts and add cheese on top.
Pour rest of mixture on chicken/cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: orange coconut cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until very light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and water, the juice and rind of orange.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, sifted together at least 2 times.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites (gently! gently!).
Bake in three layer cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put the layers together with orange and coconut filling.
Ice with any favorite white frosting.

title: layered salad
directions: Alternate layers of ingredients, leaving some bacon for top layer.

title: raisin applesauce spice cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box, then stir in one cup raisins. Pour in two round greased and floured cake pans. Cook as directed on box.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix everything by hand in order.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ice with icing recipe below when cake is cool.

title: texas "caviar"
directions: Drain peas.
Mix all ingredients and cover.
Store in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Place butter or margarine in large casserole dish in a 350° preheated oven until melted.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and milk until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into casserole with melted butter.
Next, pour fruit in the middle of the flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix margarine, milk and 3/4 of the cheese in saucepan until well blended.
Mix into potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water and let cool.
Add lemon juice and orange juice.
Blend strawberries with juice mixture until smooth in a blender or food processor. Pour into a bowl and put in freezer.
Check after 1 to 2 hours.
When top edges are frozen, blenderize again.
Freeze in bowl until firm.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spring holiday pork roast
directions: Place roast rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so bulb is in center of thickest part of roast. Roast uncovered in a 325° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160°.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, then cocoa and flour.
Mix with mixer, then fold in melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese apples
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour; cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Mix in cheese and set aside.
Combine apples, water and lemon juice; toss lightly.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over apples and pat down gently.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Add cornstarch and boil until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello, mixing well.
Let mixture completely cool, then add bananas and pecans.
Pour into unbaked graham cracker crust.
Makes two regular pies.
May top with cool whip.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs.
In greased pie dish, make a crust with crumbs and vanilla wafers.
Mix egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk and then add juice of 4 lemons.
Pour into pie dish.
Beat egg whites and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of pie and bake at 325° until slightly brown.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake with topping
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail (do not drain). Add eggs, beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, chopped nuts and coconut, as much as desired. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cake is baked, add topping.

title: life's recipe
directions: Be careful in your selection;
do not choose too young. Take only
such	varieties as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and settled, let that part remain forever settled and give your entire thought to prepare for domestic
use.
Some
insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others
are constantly getting them in hot water.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing	with patience,
well
sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Wrap well in a mantle of charity, keep warm
with
a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches
and cream.
When
thus	prepared, they will keep for years.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Note:
Ground deer burger works well instead of beef.
Just ask APCO crew.

title: shrimp in mustard sauce
directions: Season the shrimp with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil in a heavy large pan to smoking.
Over very high heat, quickly saute shrimp until they are pink.
Transfer them to a warm plate and keep warm.
To pan, add shallots and tarragon.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Deglaze the pan with sherry.
Add the cream and reduce the sauce until it coats the back of a wooden spoon.
Whisk in butter, a little at a time.
Whisk in the mustard at the last minute.
Do not let sauce boil or it will become grainy.
Serve on a platter with sauce over shrimp.
Garnish with minced chives. Serves 2.

title: oyster pepper pot
directions: *Use same amount of peppers and onions.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a microwavable dish, saute bacon until crisp.
Add green onions and potatoes; saute a few minutes.
Sprinkle with flour. Add clam juice with milk.
Bring to a boil; stir and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 8 minutes).
Add salt and pepper; stir. Add clams with liquid and whipping cream.
Heat, stir and serve. Do not overcook.
Serves 4.

title: ground chicken and curry stir-fry(use microwave to make 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Mix ground chicken with seasoned salt, 1 teaspoon curry powder and vegetable oil.
Place chicken in microsafe baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High power for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once.
Mix chicken broth with soy sauce, sesame oil, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon curry powder.
Add broccoli, snow peas and onion to chicken mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High power for 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender and liquid is boiling.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to baking dish along with the bean sprouts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Stir well. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High power for 2 to 4 minutes or until liquid has thickened.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: fannie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine; bring to a boil.
Cook 45 minutes and can.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and sugar until very stiff.
Fold in chocolate bits. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and shut off oven immediately.
Leave in oven for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Makes approximately 3 dozen kisses.

title: louisiana chef's salad
directions: Shred and chop or use food processor:

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Reserve 1 cup chicken broth.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
In saucepan, combine grated cheese, butter, soup and broth.
Heat on low until cheese melts. Line bottom
of greased 8-inch square dish with cracker crumbs. Layer broccoli, then chicken over crumbs. Cover with cheese sauce. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cheesecake
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and sugar together; put half of crust in buttered 6 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cream the cheese (should be at room temperature); add sugar and stir well.
Add well beaten egg yolks and whipped cream.
Fold in beaten egg whites to which salt has been added.
Pour over crust and cover with remaining crust.
Freeze.
This recipe can be doubled and placed in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, mandarin oranges and celery.
In another bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well. Stir this into chicken mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken breasts up into small pieces.
Mix with other ingredients, except shoestring potatoes.
Add potatoes just before serving.

title: tangy fruit dressing
directions: Gently blend sugar and lemon juice into sour cream.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients (except cornflakes & melted butter).
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Toss cornflakes with melted butter and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: enchilada aztecas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Add 2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Add chicken, avocado, tomato, olives, chilies and onion; mix well.

title: blasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 450° or whatever is max for your oven.
Cut the tough tails off of the asparagus and place the tips in an oven pan that will hold all the tips in one layer.
Pour in enough olive oil to come up 1/4th of the way on the tips.
If using the shrimp, spread them on top of the asparagus.
Put the pan in the 450° oven for 10 minutes; remove and turn the asparagus.
Check the shrimp; they might well be just as you like them at this stage.
Sprinkle the tips with a little tarragon and the juice of 1 lemon; put the pan back in the oven for 4 minutes.
Remove the pan from oven; remove asparagus from pan to a plate for serving and reserve the oil.
Put the shrimp over the asparagus and serve.
Use the oil for dipping the sourdough breadsticks.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to reach room temperature, then combine in a mixing bowl cheese and mayonnaise.
Then add pineapple, cherries and green onions.
Fold into round bowl to shape and chill for one hour.
Put chopped pecans in pie plate or one with small sides. Roll cheese ball in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: polish sausage and kraut
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers.
Cut sausage in large cubes. Put in with onions and peppers.
Drain kraut.
Pour over sausage. Let cook slow 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Divide evenly and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate until serving.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend flour and sugar, then add (a little at a time) the beer and blend, but do not overmix.
Pour in greased 1 pound loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, combine sugar, shortening and salt.
Add boiling water.
Blend and cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend. Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to egg mixture. Gradually add flour and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Add ground beef and brown. Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake(low-fat, no sugar)
directions: Toss together apples and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine honey, oil, yogurt and eggs; beat well.
Add water and vanilla. Mix remaining dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Add to the liquids.
Blend well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Beat on counter to settle.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: ortega chile and rice casserole
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients in butter.
Put half of the browned mixture in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole. Split chiles on one side only to make a pocket.
Remove any seeds; insert Monterey Jack cheese strips, cut into 4 1/2 inches long and 1 1/2-inches wide.
Put on top of rice mixture.
Cover with remaining half of rice.
Add consomme.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: mama's sweet pickle peaches
directions: Put the spices: allspice, cloves, cinnamon and ginger in a thin white cloth bag and tie top tightly.
Boil the sugar, vinegar, water and spices for 15 minutes.
Add fruit; boil until tender.
Put fruit in big jar; pour syrup over.
Pour syrup off and boil 30 minutes for next two days, then put in jars.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg and milk together and add to dry ingredients with a few swift strokes. Bake in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl, ginger ale last. Yield:
1 large bowl of punch.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Simmer potatoes, onion and celery in pot with chicken broth until very soft.
Mash or mix in blender.
Add milk, wine (if preferred) and diced carrot.
Cook until carrot is done.
Add half and half cream and bacon bits.

title: dutch cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and egg yolk and then add dry ingredients and vanilla.

title: kay's rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla and stir.
Add salt, baking powder and part of flour and mix well.
Add remaining flour.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Shape into walnut size balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten ball slightly.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat in the powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip; add fruit and mix well (do not beat).
Coloring may be added if you want more color.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
This keeps well.

title: cajun dipping sauce
directions: In a blender container, place the stewed tomatoes.
Cover and blend until nearly smooth.
In a medium saucepan, combine blended tomatoes and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in bottled hot pepper sauce.
Serve with crispy chicken bites.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and boil noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, egg, parsley, oregano and basil.
Mix beef, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Make layer of noodles, beef sauce, cottage cheese mix and both cheeses.
Continue these layers until you run out.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Make sure the water is hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat as soon as melted.

title: hearty soup
directions: Cover first 7 ingredients with 8 cups cold water; bring to boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
Then add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer one more hour.
When cool, remove bones and add meat to soup.
If soup is too thick, thin with a little cold water.
Season to taste.
Freezes well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and green pepper and chop onion finely.
Put in pan; cover and cook over medium heat until tender, stirring occasionally (20 to 30 minutes).
Add 1 stick of butter.
Cook separately 5 bacon strips and crumbled into mixture.
Beat 2 eggs and add.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put into casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Alternately add dry ingredients with buttermilk and water, blending well.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Allow it to stand in pan for 10 minutes before removing to cake plate.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and boil peppers for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix beef, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper, onion and 1/2 can tomato soup. Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in casserole dish and pour over remaining soup, diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Cook onion and pepper with thyme in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes about 3 cups.
(I sometimes use half chicken and half frozen shrimp.)

title: shrimp and bologna salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss and serve. Makes about 9 servings.

title: fluffy no-cook frosting
directions: Beat oleo, shortening and sugar until creamy.
Scald milk. Cool to lukewarm.
Add to creamed mixture and beat until spreading consistency.
Will frost 8 to 9-inch layer cake.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, white sugar, brown sugar, nutmeg, salt and oil until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs and reserve.
Add to remaining mixture the buttermilk, soda and egg.
Mix with mixer and pour into greased and floured cookie sheet with sides.
To the above reserved cake mix, add nuts and
cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking mix together glaze ingredients.

title: tarragon creamed chicken
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 1/4 cup of the butter.
Add the green onions and half of the tarragon.
Saute over medium-low heat about 5 minutes, until onions are wilted.
Add the red pepper, mushrooms, 1/2 cup of the wine and the chicken.
Increase heat to medium-high and saute about 5 minutes until chicken is opaque.
Add the shrimp and remaining tarragon.
Saute, tossing constantly, for 2 minutes until shrimp turns pink.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a separate saucepan, melt the remaining 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle flour over it when the butter bubbles and whisk to mix well.
Add half-and half, whisking vigorously over medium-low heat until sauce is smooth and thick.
Flavor with remaining 1/4 cup wine and salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Continue to cook, whisking, for 2 minutes.
Do not let boil.

title: amazing apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Spread half of apples in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Stir honey into melted oleo.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Combine wet and dry ingredients together. Crumble half of oatmeal mixture over apple slices in pan.
Cover with remaining apples.
Top with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Pour orange juice into pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate candy(my grandmother's)
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; add condensed milk and add coconut until thick.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet; bake about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add the next 4 ingredients lightly.
Add the flour, cinnamon, salt and nuts.
Blend all.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and flour. Add melted almond bark and stir in chopped nuts.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Place about 1-inch apart and bake until light brown.

title: cheddar bean dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: burnt creme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick, about 3 minutes.
Gradually beat cream into egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and pour into 6 (6 ounce) custard cups.
Place custard cups in baking pan that has about 1/2 inch water in the bottom.
Bake until set, about 45 minutes.
Remove custard cups from water and refrigerate until chilled.
Sprinkle each custard with about 2 teaspoons sugar.
Place on top rack under broiler and cook until topping is medium brown.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot wings
directions: Mix ingredients and coat wings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pat's apple coffeecake
directions: Scale milk, cool to luke warm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water (105 degrees).
Add the cooled milk.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour, beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Punch down and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in 1/2 cup margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and the remaining flour.
Beat well.
Spread dough in a greased 9 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Spoon 2 tbsp margarine and 1 tbsp sugar over dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Press apples into dough. Mix cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/2 cup sugar, sprinkle over the fruit. Bake in preheated over at 375 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: southern style biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in vinegar and milk; turn onto a floured board and knead lightly.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut biscuits and prick with a fork.
Bake on greased sheet for 12 to 15 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together and dip favorite fruit into delicious fruit dip (strawberries, grapes, kiwi, pineapple and blueberries).

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Chill one hour, then drain.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: caramel corn (microwave)
directions: Cook all ingredients, except popcorn and soda, for 3 minutes. Add soda.
Pour over popped corn in brown paper bag and shake. Cook for 1 1/2 minutes more; shake.
