Cook for another 1 1/2 minutes and shake.
Pour into serving bowl immediately and serve.

title: sweet-sour small wild game
directions: Roll the meat in salted flour and saute in margarine until browned.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until softened.
Place contents in a deep baking dish, add the remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: spicy hermits
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and eggs; add water.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves into creamed mixture.
Stir until blended.
Add dates and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with remaining 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoon milk until smooth.
Fold in half of Cool Whip, spread over crust.
Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare pudding as directed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Delish!

title: blueberry pizza pie
directions: Bake crust at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Pour over pie crust.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar; add flour and mix well. Stir in pecans. Press mixture into bottom of greased 13x9x2 inch pan. Preheat oven to 325°. Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned; cool. Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk; heat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spread over cooled crust; chill. Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate until
firm.
12 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook to 236°, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla and remove from heat. Beat by hand until it begins to thicken.
Do not beat too much! Quickly pour small patties onto wax paper.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain beans, discarding liquid.
Combine beans; toss with onion.
Make dressing by combining remaining ingredients.
Pour over beans.
Mix to coat well.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens. Salad will keep well in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken breasts with artichokes and peas
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
In 12-inch skillet over high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken until lightly browned.
Stir frequently.
Add chicken broth, wine, artichoke hearts and Prosciutto; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in peas; cook 5 minutes more or until chicken is fork-tender.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: old fashioned cocoa cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, water, vanilla and oleo.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternating with water to a creamy mix.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to sliced apples.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger mix to grill or fry
directions: Combine all ingredients, then form into patties of desired size.
These may be frozen; just put two pieces of parchment paper between patties for easy removal of desired number.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours (high for 3 to 4 hours). Serve over a small package of cooked wide egg noodles or rice.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour.
Make batter into 2 rolls and place in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Remove and slice them.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: In a blender, mix 5 bananas and lemon juice.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Last add water and sugar.
Freeze in a plastic container.
Add grapefruit soda when ready to serve.

title: fudge cake sundae
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil an 8-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in skim milk, applesauce and vanilla.
Pour batter into pan.

title: potato latkes
directions: Use a 10-inch skillet.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, mix the oleo, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar; mix well.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the buttermilk to which you have added the soda and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Batter will be thin.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together with crushed pineapple. Add chopped walnuts.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with your favorite frosting.
Enjoy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish; bake for 1 hour at 350° or until knife inserted in corn custard comes out clean.
I always double the recipe.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add raisins and milk.
Mix well and put in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, water and butter.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon butter pilaf
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan; stir in rice until well coated.
Add chicken broth, salt and lemon peel.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 minutes until fluffy. Fold in green onion, tomato and parsley.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cook stew meat until tender.
Cook until liquid is just covering meat.
In
a bowl mix together the remaining ingredients. Stir into meat.
Simemr 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish with corn tortillas.
Add chicken pieces on top of tortillas.
Combine soups, chili powder, onion and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Spread on top of chicken.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings. This can be frozen.

title: marion's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: mary's chocolate cake frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat. Can melt in microwave.
Cool several minutes.
Combine sugar and sour cream and beat until smooth.
Frost cooled cake.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling water until almost tender.
Set aside. Combine egg, Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella together.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture into each shell.
Pour a thin layer of sauce in bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange shells on top of sauce.
Continue, layering shells and sauce.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: easy cherry chocolates
directions: Line an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges of pan.
Set pan side.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: In large bowl mix oil, dill and dressing.
Add crackers and cover.
May store in brown paper bag to help absorb excess oil.

title: fat-free fantasy fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, salt and sugar together.
Add milk and corn syrup; boil this mixture until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off fire; beat well with hand mixer until it starts to thicken. Do not overbeat.
Stir in Grape-Nuts and vanilla.
Spray a 9-inch glass baking dish with nonfat cooking spray.
Pour fudge in dish; let it harden.

title: blushing party punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Freeze 4 to 5 hours.
Combine next 3 ingredients in a large punch bowl; stir well.
Add sherbet balls and ginger ale.
Stir only until blended.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cobbler(makes it's own crust)
directions: Use 1 1/2 quarts fruit slightly cooked and sweetened to taste (about 2 cups).
Use 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Pour melted margarine into bottom.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and vanilla together.
Pour all on top of butter.
Pour fruit mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: arlene and laura's hamentashen
directions: Cream the shortening with sugar and honey.
Add slightly beaten eggs and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, mix together the dry ingredients.
Add shortening mixture to dry ingredients and blend well.

title: summer sauce(salsa di estate)
directions: Fresh tomatoes and basil make this wonderful dish.

title: lemon yogurt cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet or oil lightly. Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add yogurt, egg whites, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Gradually add combined remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.
With lightly floured hands, shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Using bottom of a glass dipped in sugar, press dough into circles.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes; then remove to wire rack.
Sift confectioners sugar over warm cookies. Store in tightly covered container when cool.
Makes 4 dozen. Each cookie contains 70 calories, 2 grams fat and 45 mg. sodium.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll in balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Easy and good.

title: apple bars
directions: Cut together flour, shortening and salt as you do pie crust. Mix egg yolk with enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to flour mixture and form two balls.
Roll out one ball to fit a 10 x 15-inch (rimmed) pan.
Put corn flakes on crust and add apples. Add sugar, mixed with cinnamon, to apples.

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Into large bowl, halve cherry tomatoes and cut whole tomatoes in wedges.
Crumble Feta cheese over tomatoes.
Add sliced onion and seasonings.
Lightly coat with olive oil.
Let sit, covered, 1 to 2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place croutons in pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cook sausage, drain and crumble.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour over croutons.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix soup, cooked chicken, chilies, sour cream, milk and onions.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam and layer tortilla strips over bottom.
Add half of chicken mixture.
Cover with half of grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer until cheese turns bubbly.

title: mustard paste for baked ham
directions: Mix mustard and
sugar	with water; add flour.	Makes a thick paste.
Spread over slices of ham.	Bake.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal mix and onion in glass bowl.
Add egg and milk, stirring to combine.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot oil (375°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot.

title: hot muffin and bacon rolls
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp. Break up into bits and set aside to drain on paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl except bacon.
Add the bacon bits.
Grease bottom of cupcake tin. Spoon in batter to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° until golden brown. Serve with any meat or fish dish.

title: hawaiian beets
directions: Chop beets into small pieces.
Combine beets and pineapple in saucepan.
Mix together the flour and water and add to contents of saucepan.
Heat until thickened.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients and spread in a greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Mix the butter, sugar, crushed corn flakes and nuts; spread on top of the batter in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clay
directions: Stir soda and cornstarch together in saucepan. Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture is the consistency of moist mashed potatoes, turn onto a plate. Cover with damp cloth.
When cool, knead like dough.
Food coloring can be added. Store in Ziploc bags or margarine tubs.

title: play dough(inedible)
directions: Add a small amount of water to ingredients.
Mix like bread dough.
Can be molded and baked in a slow 200° oven, then it can be painted.
Store in airtight container in fridge to be reused.

title: warm cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Warm over low to medium heat. May add extra cinnamon and/or cloves to taste.
Serve warm.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil; add jello and cool.
When cool, add pineapple and pie filling.
Refrigerate until gelled.
For topping, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over salad.

title: rotini casserole
directions: Cook noodles per directions; drain.
Mix all other ingredients saving 1/2 of Monterey Jack cheese for topping.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 10 easily.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, nuts and margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and crumble.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip and spread over crumb crust.
Then mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk and spread over cream cheese layer.
Mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk and spread over vanilla pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: speedy sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook beef till no longer pink; drain. Add soup relish. ketchup and barbecue sauce; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine or butter in a skillet; saute onion.
Add both soups and broth, green chilies and chicken. Cook on low 10 to 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer grated cheese, then a layer of strips of corn tortilla, then a layer of sauce, then repeat layers and top with a layer of cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange coconut pie
directions: Mix together and bake in unbaked shell at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and powdered sugar. Press in bottom of a 9-inch round or square pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and milk.
Spread over graham cracker crust. Sprinkle nuts over cream cheese.
Whip the whipping cream and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over nut layer.
Then spread pie filling over the nuts.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: southwestern cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and seasonings in bowl; mix well. Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or just pat over ball. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with Ritz or Wheat Thins.

title: glorified chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a 2-quart baking dish.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken. Bake 20 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Stir sauce before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then mix in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, pickles and 1 egg.
Moisten with salad dressing.
Season to taste.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked egg.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours (may be cooked on high for 4 to 6 hours).
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 4.
Serve with a tossed salad.
Makes a complete meal.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Soak cauliflower in salt water (2 tablespoons salt), drain and rinse; mix with rest of vegetables.
Sprinkle dressing mix over vegetables; add sour cream and mix well.

title: monster cookies
directions: In large mixing
bowl
combine	all
ingredients in the order given.
Roll into balls and place on well-greased cookie sheet. Flatten ball with
a
glass
which	has been dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for
to 12 minutes.
Depending on the size of the cookie,
this
recipe
makes
a
large batch!
The dough or finished cookie can be frozen.

title: simple chicken italiano
directions: In a large skillet, combine chicken and about 1/3 of the Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover.
Simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 5.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare crust and place into 9-inch pie pan.
In large bowl, combine sugars, flour, cornmeal and salt. Set aside.
In mixer bowl, combine eggs, butter, milk and vanilla until just mixed (do not form bubbles).
Combine with sugar mixture and blend until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle top with coconut and nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly puffed and golden brown.
Remove from oven to cool.
Makes 8 servings.
Do not let the name fool you!

title: oatmeal chocolate chip wheat germ cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat. Add flour, wheat germ, baking soda and powder.
Beat.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish (or other).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Blend sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 the container of whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Combine pudding and milk and beat 2 minutes.
Pour over cooled mixture and let set in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
Top with remainder of whipped topping.

title: mom's goulash
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook carrots to done (keep water). Simmer in oil in frying pan the chopped or sliced onion and green pepper until soft.
Boil spaghetti until done.
Keep water.
Fry ground beef until red is gone.
Put all in large roasting pan using water from both carrots and spaghetti (use own judgement as to how much water) along with tomato paste and sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir through to mix gently so spaghetti stays long.
Ingredients will be soupy.
Then bake on low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Will have to stir occasionally.
Will get thickened. Add vegetables.

title: italian garden vegetable soup
directions: Brown 4 to 6 boneless chicken thighs or 2 to 3 boneless chicken breasts with basil, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Cut/dice into bite size pieces. Combine broth, tomatoes (undrained) and vegetables in large soup pot. Bring to boil. Add chicken and simmer until chicken is done. Add tortellini and heat through. Serve with Parmesan cheese and a crusty French loaf.

title: white chili
directions: Simmer mushrooms and onion in enough broth to cover.
Add beans, chicken, salsa and cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts. Thin with broth if too thick.
Taste before adding salt and pepper.

title: chocolate cinnamon cake
directions: Mix water, oleo, shortening and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Mix this in a large bowl with sugar and flour.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 2-quart microproof casserole, combine green onions, celery, green pepper, butter and garlic.
Cook covered on High 3 minutes or until onions are transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook covered on Medium or reheat 6 to 7 minutes. Stir, cook covered on Medium heat or reheat until hot.
Let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: texan-size almond crunch cookies
directions: Blend sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil until well mixed. Add almond extract and eggs; mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Gradually blend in all flours, soda, salt and cream of tartar at low speed. By hand, stir in almonds and brickle chips. For easier handling, refrigerate dough about 30 minutes. Shape into balls; roll in sugar. Place 5 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. With fork dipped in sugar, flatten in crisscross pattern. Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown around edges. Cool cookies 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet. Makes 3 1/2 dozen (4 inch) cookies.

title: summer vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion in oil until tender. Add the next eight ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 - 30 or until vegetables are tender. Stir in celery leaves and tomato paste. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: unusual frozen cake
directions: Add milk instead of water to cake mix, using the same amount as box instructs for water.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Do not bake. Cover pan with foil or tight fitting lid and freeze overnight.
The next day, combine brown sugar, cocoa, boiling water and vanilla. Stir well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take cake from freezer; remove foil and pour cocoa mixture over frozen cake.
Immediately bake for 1 hour or until done.
Cool.

title: soy cheese enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In one skillet, warm the enchilada sauce.
Coat the bottom of a shallow baking dish with a little of the enchilada sauce.
In second skillet, brush bottom with a small amount of oil (to keep tortilla from sticking).
Heat skillet. Prepare one tortilla at a time.
Place tortillas in skillet, one at a time, in hot oil.
Hold in skillet 3 to 5 seconds, until soft. Then with tongs, quickly turn to soften the other side. Immediately dip tortilla in skillet with the warming enchilada sauce.
Hold in skillet just for a second or the tortilla will tear.
Place tortilla on plate and spoon soy Cheddar, soy Monterey Jack and onion toward one edge of the tortilla.
Roll up tightly and place seam side down in the baking dish.
When all of the tortillas are filled and in baking dish, pour remaining enchilada sauce over them and sprinkle with soy cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes or until soy cheese has melted and enchiladas are heated through.

title: stuffed peppers(crockery cooking)
directions: Boil 6 quarts water in deep pan.
Cut 7 peppers; strip and remove seeds.
Chop 1 pepper for sauce.
Put peppers and tops into pan and boil until slightly limp (save 3 cups water).
Put in large skillet 2 tablespoons oil, beef, pork, chopped green pepper, onion, garlic, salt, oregano and sugar and saute until pink color has left meat (slightly browned).
Use 2 cups of water used to cook peppers to cook 1 cup rice and salt.
Mix rice and meat mixture and stuff the 6 remaining peppers, securing tops with toothpicks.
Add remaining rice mixture to tomatoes, sauce and tomato paste.
Put peppers in crock-pot and pour sauce over top. Cover and cook on high 1 hour; turn to low and cook 6 to 8 hours until done.
Serve with cole slaw and French bread.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef in fat with onion.
Add and cook 10 minutes the beans and soup.
Make into paste and blend in the chili powder, flour, water and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tallarine casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain.
In casserole dish, add meat, creamed corn, tomato soup, noodles and olives.
Mix and add soup can of water.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°, then uncover and bake for 15 more minutes.
Top with cheese, let melt and serve. Serves 4 to 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in large pan; bring to rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper. Let cool. Yields 40.

title: thin white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Makes 4 cups.

title: one pan chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in an 8 to 9-inch square pan.
Beat with fork until smooth and creamy.
Scrape bottom and sides after 1 minute of beating.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Great served warm.

title: barbara bush's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt onto wax paper.
Beat butter, sugars and egg in large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in hot water and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended and smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by well rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto large greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool on sheet on wire rack 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Makes 3 dozen.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is all gone; cool.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and cooking oil; mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour; mix well.
Place in well greased tube or Bundt pan.
I use tube pan and put a layer of waxed paper on bottom.
I took out of pan as soon as it was baked but took a knife and went around circle twice before taking out of pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Keep baking until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from heat and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Spread over bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together soup, celery, onion and mayonnaise and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with almonds.
Top with the dry stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken with water chestnuts and celery.
Stir soy sauce into mayonnaise; combine with chicken mixture.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium high heat and cook beef until browned, stirring often.
Set beef aside.
Add remaining oil to skillet and add onion; cook until tender.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in soup, sour cream and paprika.
Heat to soft boil, return beef to skillet and heat through.
Serve over noodles, garnishing with parsley.

title: creamy coffee cooler
directions: Put milk, coffee, sweetener and vanilla into blender.
Blend. Add ice slowly until mixture is thick and frothy.
Makes 2 servings, 43 calories each.

title: ooey, gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine and pat down in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and pecans well and pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Leave in pan and cut into bars after they cool.

title: cherry chocolate chip nut cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Fold in pie filling, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until top is well browned. Serves 8.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Combine orange juice, lemon juice, oil, soy sauce and pepper in bowl.
Rinse and dry chicken.
Add chicken to marinade and turn to coat well.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight. Grill chicken 20 minutes until tender.
Brush occasionally with marinade.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in meat loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered steak roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into
6 pieces (about 8 x 4-inch).
Pound with meat hammer.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing near center of each piece of meat. Roll up. Tuck in ends and fasten with toothpicks.
Add soup and water. Cover and cook over low heat 1 1/4 hours or until tender. Stir now and then.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in milk, vanilla, eggs and melted butter.
Blend well with electric mixer.
Stir in 1 cup coconut and 1/2 cup pecans (reserve remaining coconut and pecans to garnish pie).
Pour mixture into pie shell (unbaked). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool throughly.
Whip cream until peaks form; spoon on top of pie.
Toast remaining nuts and coconut and sprinkle on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put in a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: chestnuts - buckeyes
directions: Knead, using hands, first four ingredients to dough like consistency.
Roll into small balls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.

title: amish steak
directions: Mix hamburger, crumbs and water.
Put on baking sheet; refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet.
Put in roaster and pour mushroom soup over meat.
Bake at 350° until done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except gravy.
Shape into 6 oblong patties.
In skillet, brown patties in shortening, pour off fat.
Add gravy.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender but not browned.
Add broccoli with sauce, chicken broth, cream and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg and mix with other ingredients. Add cold water until medium texture (milk optional). Spoon into hot oil (drop in small amount to test oil). Remove when brown and drain onto paper towels.
Makes about two dozen.

title: apple caramel dessert
directions: In double boiler (top) heat caramel and Pet milk.
Stir flour, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and butter.
Blend in bowl, 1 egg, water and oil together, then pour in flour mixture.
Set aside.
Blend 1/3 cup sugar, lemon rinds and apples with 1/3 cup flour.
Use 16 to 18 inches of foil.

title: home fried potato
directions: Slice potato (thin) and cook in butter; add water.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; cut up 1 cup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup water gradually until smooth.
Add cut up berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Stir in a few drops red food color.
Cool. Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for garnish.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with topping and berries.

title: haiti caribbean rice and beans
directions: Soak overnight or by quick method 2 cups dry pigeon peas, pinto beans or kidney beans, water and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer just until tender, about 40 minutes.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Heat in large covered skillet the oil or margarine; add garlic, green onions, tomato, parsley, pepper and drained beans.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add rice and reserved bean liquid.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook 20 to 25 minutes without stirring.

title: chicken hula
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rub chicken with garlic and salt.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan.
Add honey, lime juice, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add pineapple slices and heat.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
In morning, bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together.
Blend together fruit cocktail, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 egg, 1/2 cup juice and nuts.
Stir two mixtures together and pour into medium pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar over the top.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place drained fruit in 8 x 8-inch baking dish (do not grease). Combine flour, sugar, oats and nuts. Mix in butter or margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden. Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Next, include all ingredients together and cook, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil 4 cups rice in 1 gallon of water, until rice is semi-soft (want it to be a little hard).
Drain water, cut up stick of margarine and stir into rice along with 1 cup of sugar.
Set aside.
Heat half and half on top of stove.
Do not boil.
Let it come to a boil, then add to rice mixture along with 6 tablespoons of vanilla extract.
Stir entire mixture.
Put into preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
After 45 minutes, stir entire mixture and add 2 more tablespoons vanilla and raisins, if you want to.
Cook at 350° for 30 more minutes or until mixture sets.

title: coconut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream butter and both sugars together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and unbeaten eggs (one at a time) and mix together well. Add flour, salt and baking soda and mix together. Add chopped nuts and coconut; mix about 30 to 40 seconds. Add chocolate chips, not mixing any longer than 30 seconds. Drop cookies 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkie cakes longways. Place in bowl, filling side up. Pour pudding over Twinkies; top with crushed pineapple (drained), then cut up and put on top of pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.

title: creamy chicken with angel hair
directions: Brown chicken on all sides in oil in large skillet.
Remove from skillet.
Cook and stir vegetables and garlic in same skillet over medium heat, 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in sauce and wine.
Add chicken and cover.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: spice nuts
directions: Toast nuts for 8 minutes.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and cook until soft stage.
Add nuts to syrup.
Stir until sugary.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: batter buns
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, egg and 1 cup flour.
Mix by hand.
Add the remaining 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons flour.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into a greased muffin pan about 1/2 full.
Pat with a little flour and cover with a cloth.
Let rise in a warm place about 40 minutes.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 15 buns.

title: easy rigatoni
directions: Cook and drain the pasta.
Mix with half the sauce, the cottage cheese, half the Parmesan and the optional ingredient(s). Pour into a baking dish and top with the remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: italian egg pie
directions: Beat eggs and milk together until blended. Add tuna, cheese, salt, pepper, basil and oregano. Stir well.
Spoon into pie crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot, cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer croutons, mushrooms, sausage and cheese.
Mix milk and soup and pour over casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Drain the fruit, reserving the juice, and puree in blender. Add enough reserved juice from the can to make 1 cup.
Combine the puree and gelatin in a saucepan.
Wait for one minute until the gelatin is softened, then cook, stirring, over low heat until the gelatin is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar substitute. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup, 9 calories per tablespoon.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut 2 pieces heavy-duty foil; place chicken breast in center of each.
Top with onion and remaining ingredients.
Wrap well; place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 2 servings.

title: roast prime ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place meat in shallow open roasting pan.
Sprinkle with flour; rub into meat.
Season generously with salt and pepper.
Place a tent of foil loosely over top of roast. Place in hot oven.
Roast for 9 minutes (medium) per pound.
When roasting time is up, turn off oven heat.
Do not open oven door. Let roast remain in oven for at least 1 hour.

title: corn noodles
directions: Put all ingredients into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven or grill fried potatoes(four or six servings)
directions: Spray Pam on heavy-duty foil (about 20 x 20-inch).
Place potatoes on foil, salt and pepper to taste.
Add sliced onions on top and 1/2 stick butter (slice over top).
Fold foil up around potatoes, seal the edges with foil.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring every 20 minutes.
Also good placed on grill.
Very good with steak or fish.

title: sesame and soy vegetable stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger; set aside.
In large skillet over medium heat toast sesame seed until light brown, stirring constantly.
Pour sesame seed into small bowl; set aside.
Heat same skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add oil; heat until it ripples.
Add broccoli and cauliflower; stir-fry 2 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir broth mixture into vegetables; add onions.
Cover; simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Spoon into serving dish; sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef burgundy(dutch recipe)
directions: Cut steak into cubes. Shake with flour and coat evenly.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Brown the meat and remove from heat.
Add onion, parsley, garlic, bay leaves, salt and pepper. Stir in mushrooms, red wine and water.
Heat.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours until the meat is tender. Remove bay leaves. Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover this mixture with diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco until creamy; add eggs, then add milk, soda and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; gradually add flour mixture to cream mixture.
You should be able to roll dough when mixed.
Roll and cut into 1/4-inch slices and decorate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked iowa cornfed coon
directions: Place the carcasses on a rack in a roaster (I prefer an electric self-basting type).
Add bouillon; salt and pepper.
Add bay leaves and other herbs and chilies.
Strip with salt pork or fat back.
Place lemon and onions slices over the meat.
Sprinkle the garlic over the meat.
Add the chopped celery.
Cook at 350° for an hour or until meat is done.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Put 1/2 of cheese, onion and taco sauce in layers in pan, then put remainder of cheese.
Top with sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.
Reheat if it gets cold.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing and butter over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 3 cheese macaroni
directions: Add macaroni and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Cook until macaroni is tender; drain.
Add in separate dish milk, sour cream, 3/4 cheese, egg, margarine and salt to taste.
Mix well, then add macaroni to mixture.
Pour into a baking dish or pan.
Add remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° until top cheese melts and light or golden brown.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Select number of pork chops needed for your meal.
Top each pork chop with thin slice of lemon and onion; sprinkle on a bit of brown sugar and dot with ketchup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Great main dish served with baked sweet potatoes, shredded beets and a green salad.

title: country cream-style corn
directions: Cook corn in a small amount of water.
Add salt, sugar and cream.
Bring to boil and thicken with mixture of cornstarch and a little cream.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Shake chicken pieces in bag with flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt oleo in shallow baking pan in 375° oven.
Add chicken.
Turn to coat.
Then arrange in pan, skin side down.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken. Bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
If chicken cannot be served immediately, brush with melted oleo and leave in oven, reducing heat to 300°.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and spices for 20 minutes.
Drop fruit in a few at a time.
Cool and serve.

title: rosy lemonade punch
directions: Let berries thaw and put through sieve if you wish.
Combine concentrate of lemonade with berries and berry juice. Add ginger ale and sparkling water just before serving.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Sliced bananas make an interesting garnish for this rosy lemonade punch.
Makes about 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: quick bread pudding
directions: Pour warm milk over the bread cubes and raisins; set aside. Mix the rest of the ingredients well and add to the bread mixture. Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
(You may add chopped nuts or cut-up apple to the pudding if desired.)
Serves 6.

title: hot cheesy potato salad
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, green peppers and hot dogs.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In bowl, combine sour cream, flour, salt and mustard.
Stir into skillet. Heat 5 minutes but do not boil.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat, covered, until cheese melts.

title: pasta in white clam sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti to desired doneness.
Meanwhile, put the wine, water, shallots and garlic in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add the fresh clams.
Cover and continue to cook over medium heat.
Remove the clams when their shells have opened.
Stir the broth from the canned clams into saucepan.
Cook a few minutes more.
Reduce heat to low and whisk in buttermilk and cornstarch mixture.
Cook for about 2 minutes more to thicken, whisking constantly.
Stir in the Parmesan cheese, canned clams, oregano, basil, pepper, hot sauce and chopped parsley.

title: applesauce banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and mix with sugar; let stand for 15 minutes. Mix all ingredients and stir in banana mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: famous tomato sauce
directions: Smash garlic cloves lightly with a knife, but don't chop. Heat olive oil and garlic on medium heat.
Don't let garlic burn. Remove stem ends of tomatoes.
Crush tomatoes with a fork and add to oil.
Add salt to taste, and basil and parsley, if used.
Heat on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Voila!

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients alternately with the next 4 ingredients, sifted together.
Add the last 3 ingredients.
Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys (Proverbs 23:14; beat), and you will have a good cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green tortillas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, drain. Combine hamburger and onion with peminto, taco sauce, chicken soup, mushroom soup, and chilies.

title: hot and heavenly chili
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in a skillet until onions are light brown.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain off excess grease.
In a large pot, add beans, ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Add 4 to 6 tablespoons chili powder.
Add tomato sauce.
Add 4 to 6 more tablespoons chili powder.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: after school treat
directions: Pour 1/2 cup powdered sugar into bowl.
Add milk a little at a time and stir.
Add more milk until icing thickens.
Spoon onto 1/2 graham cracker. Place the other 1/2 graham cracker on top.

title: salsa
directions: In a food processor, chop until the ingredients are diced. Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Spray deep pie dish with nonstick spray.
Beat ingredients and pour over vegetables in pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Prepare package cheese sauce according to directions on back adding 3/4 cup more milk.
Layer 3 lasagna noodles in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or lasagna pan sprayed with Pam.
Layer cottage cheese, carrots and onions, then spinach (will need to squeeze out any excess water).
Place 3 more noodles, layering any remaining vegetables and cottage cheese.
Layer 3 more noodles and pour cheese sauce mix over this, then top with entire bag of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the powdered sugar and peanut butter together.
Cook the flour, sugar, salt, eggs, butter or oleo and scalded milk together. Add half of the powdered sugar and peanut butter to this mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put the other half on top of the mixture.
Brown meringue.

title: strawberry buttermilk shake
directions: Combine strawberries, vanilla, honey, sugar, orange juice concentrate, buttermilk and ice cubes in blender.
Blend at high speed in 3 to 4 (30 second) bursts until mixture is light and frothy.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine instant pudding mix, pineapple with juice, sour cream and sugar in deep narrow bowl.
Beat slowly with beater (1 minute). Pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping or pineapple chunks or cherries.

title: teriyaki wings
directions: Combine catsup, molasses, vinegar, soy sauce, and mustard. Mix well. Dip wings in sauce and place close together in shallow baking dish. Pour any remaining sauce over wings and cover closely with lid or foil.

title: fresh apple loaf
directions: Combine apples, pecans and sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring often and do not drain. Combine flour, soda, salt and spices in a large bowl. Add apple mixture; stir well. Stir in butter, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets and save liquid.
Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar and beet liquid or water; stir over low heat until thickened.
Add beets and butter.
Heat.
Makes about 5 servings.
